{"title_page": "Alfred Brauner", "text_new": "{{Infobox academic\n| honorific_prefix   = Doctor of Philosophy \n| name               = Alfred Brauner\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| birth_name         = <!-- use only if different from full/othernames -->\n| birth_date         = {{birth date|1910|7|3|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Saint-Mand\u00e9]], [[Val-de-Marne]], [[France]]\n| death_date         = {{death date and age|2002|12|01|1910|07|03}}\n| death_place        = [[Paris]], [[France]]\n| death_cause        = \n| nationality        = Austrian \n| citizenship        = French \n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = \n| period             = \n| known_for          =  [[child psychology]] ; [[Autism]] ; [[Sociology of childhood]]\n| home_town          = \n| title              = \n| boards             = <!--board or similar positions extraneous to main occupation-->\n| spouse             = \n| partner            = \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| awards             = <!--notable national-level awards only-->\n| website            = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[University of Vienna]] ; [[University of Paris]] <!--will often consist of the linked name of the last-attended higher education institution-->\n| thesis_title       = \n| thesis_url         = \n| thesis_year        = \n| school_tradition   = \n| doctoral_advisor   = \n| academic_advisors  = \n| influences         = <!--must be referenced from a third-party source-->\n| era                = \n| discipline         = \n| sub_discipline     = <!--academic discipline specialist area \u2013 e.g. Sub-atomic research, 20th-century Danish specialist, Pauline research, Arcadian and Ugaritic specialist-->\n| workplaces         = <!--full-time positions only, not student positions-->\n| doctoral_students  = <!--only those with WP articles-->\n| notable_students   = <!--only those with WP articles-->\n| main_interests     = \n| notable_works      = \n| notable_ideas      = \n| influenced         = <!--must be referenced from a third-party source-->\n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Alfred Brauner''' (3 July 1910 - 1 December 2002) was an [[Austria|Austrian-born]] French [[scholar]], [[sociologist]], [[child psychologist]] and [[author]],   who was a volunteer in the [[International Brigades]] during the [[Spanish Civil War]]<ref name=\"\u00d6sterreicher\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.doew.at/erinnern/biographien/spanienarchiv-online/spanienfreiwillige-b/brauner-alfred-dr |title=\u00d6sterreicherInnen f\u00fcr Spaniens Freiheit 1936-1939 |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://www.doew.at/|publisher=Dokumentationsarchiv des \u00f6sterreichischen Widerstandes}}</ref> and a [[French Resistance]] member during [[Occupied France]]. He has devoted his life to educating refugee, displaced and maladjusted children, participating in the welcoming of Jewish child survivors of the [[Kristallnacht]] and of the [[Nazi concentration camps]] of [[Buchenwald]] and [[Auschwitz]] from 1939 to 1946<ref name=\"L'accueil\">{{cite book | author = Brauner Alfred, Brauner Fran\u00e7oise| title = L\u2019accueil des enfants survivants| page= | publisher = Cahiers du groupement de recherches pratiques pour l'enfance | year = 1994 | isbn = 978-0-7914-0453-9}}</ref>. An early writer on infantile autism,  he also pioneered the analysis of children\u2019s drawings in war, creating from 1938 the first collection of drawing-testimonials<ref name=dessin\u00e9>{{cite book | author = Brauner Alfred, Fran\u00e7oise| title = J\u2019ai dessin\u00e9 la guerre. Le dessin de l'enfant dans la guerre | page= | publisher = Elsevier| year = 1991 | isbn = 2-7046-1378-8}}</ref> to offer a unique perspective of the major conflicts of the [[20th century]] through the eyes of children.<ref name=\"Bio\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Brauner | first1 = Alfred | authorlink = Alfred Brauner| title = Biographie du docteur Fran\u00e7oise Brauner| doi = 10.3917/sn.018.0167.| journal = Sud/Nord| volume = 18 | issue = 1 | pages = 167\u201373| year = 2003 | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>.\n \n==Background in Austria and education==\n \nBorn in 1910 in [[Saint-Mand\u00e9]] to [[Austro-Hungarian]] parents spending two years in [[France]] for professional reasons, Alfred Brauner comes from a prestigious Viennese family. <ref name=\" Brauner Claude-Michel\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.enfance-violence-exil.net/fichiers_sgc/BRAUNER.pdf |title=Alfred et Fran\u00e7oise Brauner par leur fils |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= publisher=}}</ref>  In Vienna, his family held private classical music concerts at the [[Palais Esterh\u00e1zy]], where [[Sigmund Freud]] was invited. <ref name==\"Cyrulnik >{{cite book | author =Cyrulnik Boris | title = De Chair et d'\u00e2me | page= 229 | publisher = \u00c9ditions Odile Jacob | year = 2006  | isbn = }}</ref><ref name=\"Brauner Claude-Michel \" /> In his childhood, he experienced himself the repercussions of the war and witnessed his father leaving for the [[First World War]] to serve in the Austro-Hungarian army. <ref name=\"L'accueil\"/> To save him from the epidemics, during the First World War, his parents sent him to a family in [[Moravia]]. <ref name=\"L'accueil\"/> He defended his doctoral thesis in philosophy at the [[University of Vienna]] in 1934, entitled \"The Unanimism of Jules Romains,\" a correspondence starting between the young Viennese doctoral student and [[Jules Romains]]. <ref name=\"Yannick Ripa\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Ripa | first1 = Yannick | authorlink = Yannick Ripa| title = Naissance du dessin de guerre. Les \u00e9poux Brauner et les enfants de la guerre civile espagnole | doi = 10.3917/ving.089.0029 | journal = Vingti\u00e8me Si\u00e8cle. Revue d\u2019Histoire| volume = 89 | issue = 1 | pages = 29\u201346| year = 2006 | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>. Alfred served in the French army from 1939 and was decorated with the [[Croix de Guerre 1939-1945]]. <ref name=\"\u00c0 Alfred Brauner \">{{Cite journal | last1 = Perrier | first1 = Edmond | authorlink = Edmond Perrier| title = \u00c0 Alfred Brauner| doi =  | journal = Sud/ Nord| volume = 18  | issue = 1  | pages = 11-11 | year = 2003 | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref> In 1946, he defended a thesis at the [[University of Paris]] on \u201cThe Psychic Repercussions of Modern War on Childhood\"<ref name=\"Yannick Ripa\"/> and the same year presented a complementary thesis entitled \"Plan, Organization and Results of the Rehabilitation Center for Juvenile Offenders in Kaiserebersdorf near Vienna (Austria). \" His younger brother William emigrated to the [[United States]] before the beginning of the [[Second World War]] and died on October 6, 1948 in the [[1948 Georgia USAF Boeing B-29 crash]], which resulted in the US court case [[United States v. Reynolds]]. <ref name=\"LA Times\">{{Cite journal | last1 =Siegel  | first1 =Barry  | authorlink = | title = A Daughter Discovers What Really Happened | doi = | journal = Los Angeles Times | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2004  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref><ref name=\"LA\">{{Cite journal | last1 =Barry  | first1 = Siegel  | authorlink = | title = How the Death of Judy\u2019s Father Made America More Secretive | doi = | journal = Los Angeles Times | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2004  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref><ref name=\"legal affairs\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Freedman  | first1 = Michael  | authorlink = | title = Daughters of the Cold War. Three women sue the Air Force for covering up the deaths of their fathers in a 1948 test flight. | doi = | journal = Legal Affairs | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2004  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\n\nAlfred began his professional activity as an educator in a rehabilitation center for juvenile offenders at Kaiserebersdorf in [[Vienna]] from 1928 to 1933. <ref name=\"Mintec\">{{Cite web|url= https://docplayer.fr/80750089-Fonds-brauner-repertoire-numerique-alfred-et-francoise-brauner.html |title= FONDS BRAUNER:REPERTOIRE NUMERIQUE |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= publisher=' }}</ref> During the [[Spanish Civil War]], Alfred Brauner volunteered in the [[International Brigades]] and was placed at the head of a committee to help evacuees or refugees, because of his previous experience with at-risk youth.<ref name=\"L'accueil\"/><ref name=\"\u00d6sterreicher\"/><ref name=\"Barcelona\">{{Cite web|url=http://sidbrint.ub.edu/en/content/brauner-alfred |title= DADES DEL BRIGADISTA. BRAUNER, Alfred |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= http://sidbrint.ub.edu/en publisher=Barcelona University}}</ref><ref name=\"Sugarman\">{{Cite web|url= https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/History/spanjews.pdf |title= Against Fascism - Jews who served in The International Brigade in the Spanish Civil War |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org publisher=Jewish Virtual Library}}</ref> It is a home for children evacuated from Madrid and Asturias after the [[bombing of Guernica]], the goal being to help the Spanish children of Republican territories, in the country and in the combat zone.<ref name=\"L'accueil\"/><ref name=thesis>{{cite book | author =Brauner Alfred | title =The Psychic Repercussions of Modern War on Childhood| page= | publisher =University of Paris La Sorbonne | year = 1946  | isbn = }}</ref> Finally, Alfred returned to France after the defeat of the [[Spanish Republic]].<ref name=\"\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Requeno Gallego | first1 = Manuel   | last2 = Sep\u00falveda Losa     | first2 = Rosa Mar\u00eda | authorlink = | title = La sanidad en las Brigadas Internacionales | doi = | journal = Ediciones de la Universidad de Castilla-La Mancha | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2006  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>><ref name=\"Lefebvre\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Lefebvre  | first1 = Michel  | last2 = Latorre | first2 = Marga | authorlink = | title = Las brigadas internacionales : im\u00e1genes recuperadas | doi = | journal = Lunwerg Editores | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2003  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>\n\nIn 1938, Alfred Brauner and his wife Fritzi discovered the trauma of child victims of war after receiving a set of drawings from a class in Barcelona. These were, in addition to Catalan schoolchildren who were fortunate enough to stay in their school, refugees from Madrid who had witnessed tragic events. The Brauners made a pedo-psychiatric analysis of the child's drawing, a privileged mode of graphic expression of the young child, highlighting what seems to them characteristic of the child's drawing in the war, taking notes, creating medical records and questionnaires. Drawings and writings of children of the Spanish War were the result of a contest organized by Alfred Brauner among the children of Barcelona in 1938 on three themes: \"My life Before the War\", \"What I Saw from the War\" and \"How I See My Life after the War\". <ref name=thesis/>. It was then the beginning of their work on \"children who have lived through the war.\" 4000 drawings of refugee children and numerous essays were collected in Spain, which later, along with other drawings of children in war, offered a unique testimony of the conflicts of the 20th century through the eyes of children. <ref name=\"\">{{Cite journal | last1 =Ibarz Serrat  | first1 = Virgilio  | authorlink = | title = Los dibujos infantiles de la guerra 1937-1938: el caso de la ni\u00f1a de Ballobar | doi = | journal = Diario del AltoArag\u00f3n | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2009  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>. Their project to publish drawings and testimonies of children in war received the support of [[Ilya Ehrenburg]] and [[Romain Rolland]] who \"regarded this collection as of considerable educational, historical and human interest.\" <ref name=\"Yannick Ripa\"/>\n \nIn 1939, Alfred Brauner welcomed 130 Jewish children from the Palatinate, Berlin and Austria, <ref name=\"L'accueil\"/> survivors of the [[Kristallnacht]] at La Guette, a French castle owned by the Rothschild family and made available by [[Baroness Germaine de Rothschild]]. <ref name=\"La Guette\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.ajpn.org/sauvetage-Chateau-de-la-Guette-245.html |title= Ch\u00e2teau de la Guette durant la Seconde Guerre mondiale (WWII) |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= http://www.ajpn.org/index.php | publisher= }}</ref><ref name=\"\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Lochy  | first1 = Emilie | authorlink = | title = Extrait de l'ouvrage : Enfances en guerre - T\u00e9moignages d'enfants sur la guerre | doi = | journal = Le Cercle Psy | volume = 12  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2014 | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>. Alfred\u2019s  intention was to analyze the problems posed in working with children traumatized by their experiences and by separation from their families, with the aim of adapting them to a new life and preparing them for integration into France. <ref name=\"L'accueil\"/> He then described this educational experience in his state thesis, defended in 1946, entitled \"The Psychic Repercussions of Modern War on Childhood.\" <ref name=thesis/>\n \nFrom January 1941, Alfred Brauner entered the [[French Resistance]] and welcomed the [[Austrian resistance]]\u2019s leadership in his [[Rue Bonaparte]] apartment in [[Paris]].<ref name=\"Resistance\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Brauner  | first1 = Fran\u00e7oise Erna  | authorlink = | title = L'an\u00e9antissement de deux r\u00e9seaux de la r\u00e9sistance | doi = 10.3917/sn.018.0034\n | journal = Sud/Nord | volume = 18  | issue = 1  | pages = 34-48 | year = 2003  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref><ref name=\"Bio\"/> With members of the [[\u00d6sterreichische Freiheitsfront]] arriving every morning at a specific time, Alfred Brauner decided to open a German Language course as a cover from [[Gestapo]]. <ref name=\"Resistance\"/> In 1945, he helped welcoming and educating 444 surviving boys from the [[Auschwitz]] and [[Buchenwald]] [[concentration camps]], in the scope of the [[Oeuvre de Secours aux Enfants]] (O.S.E.) in [[Ecouis]], [[France]]. This welcoming of Buchenwald's child survivors in children's homes inspired the script of the film [[Nina\u2019s House]],<ref name=\" \">{{Cite web|url= https://jeudisducinema.be/La-maison-de-Nina |title= La maison de Nina |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://jeudisducinema.be/ | publisher=Les jeudis du cinema }}</ref> as well as the documentary [[The Boys of Buchenwald]].\n \nIn 1950, Alfred Brauner created the \"Practical Research for Children,\" which brings together professionals of childhood in order to develop medico-pedagogical methods intended for the education of children with mental disabilities.<ref name=\"Mintec\"/>. In 1955, he founded a day hospital for mentally and physically handicapped children located in the center of Paris, then transferred to Saint-Mand\u00e9, and worked on the rehabilitation of these children, giving priority to their education. <ref name=\"Bio\"/> Alfred Brauner was the ambassador of the association \"Children Refugees of the World,\" as well as the only non-physician president of the Society of Expression Psychopathology and Art Therapy. <ref name=\"SFPE\">{{Cite web|url= https://www.sfpe-art-therapie.fr/Quelques-dates-qui-marquent-les-avancees-sur-trois-voies-paralleles_a34.html |title= Quelques dates qui marquent les avanc\u00e9es sur trois voies parall\u00e8les. La voie hexagonale |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://www.sfpe-art-therapie.fr/ | publisher=SFPE}}</ref><ref name=\"BNF\">{{Cite web|url= https://catalogue.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb118938323 |title= Notice de personne. Brauner, Alfred (1910-2002) |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://catalogue.bnf.fr/index.do | publisher=Biblioth\u00e8que nationale de France}}</ref> He was awarded the [[Hans Prinzhorn]] medal of the \"German-speaking Society for the Psychopathology of Expression\" in 1976. <ref name=\"Prinzhorn\">{{Cite web|url= https://www.dgpa.org/prinzhorn.php?m=6 |title= Preistr\u00e4ger der Hans Prinzhorn Medaille |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://www.dgpa.org/  |publisher=''Deutschsprachige Gesellschaft\nf\u00fcr Kunst & Psychopathologie des Ausdrucks e.V.''}}</ref> In 1986, [[Jacques Chaban-Delmas]] offered him the medal of the city of [[Bordeaux]]. <ref name=\" Brauner Claude-Michel\"/>\n \nOver the course of their career, the Brauners have analyzed children's drawings collected from around the world from children in about 20 countries at war, including the Boer War, the First World War, the Spanish War, Nazi Germany, Poland 1939, concentration camps, Hiroshima-Nagasaki, Polisario, the Israeli-Palestinian Conflict, the Lebanon War, the Algerian War, the Western Sahara War, El Salvador, Afghanistan, the Gulf War, Bosnia, and Chechnya. <ref name=dessin\u00e9/>.\n \nFrom 18 January to 10 February 1999, at the [[UNESCO]] headquarters in [[Paris]], an  exhibition was held with more than 200 drawings of children who lived through  war. Entitled \"I\u2019ve Drawn the War. A Century of Drawings of Children in Wars (1900-1999), under the high sponsorship and under the patronage of [[Simone Veil]], these drawings-testimonials belonging to the Brauner collection revealed the impact of the extreme violence of war for the child.<ref name=\"Enfances en guerre\">{{Cite web|url= https://magasindesenfants.hypotheses.org/2215\n |title= Enfances en guerre. T\u00e9moignages d\u2019enfants sur la guerre |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= |publisher=Open Edition}}</ref> This exhibition, which was considered part of the \"World Heritage,\" was then shown in Hiroshima, Jerusalem, Budapest, Vienna and more than 40 cities in Germany.  From 7 to 9 December 2011, a tribute to the 100th anniversary of the birth of the Brauners (1911-2011) was organized at UNESCO Headquarters, with the organization of an international colloquium entitled '' Childhood in War. Testimonies from Children about War.''<ref name=\"UNESCO \">{{Cite web|url= http://www.unesco.org/new/fr/unesco/events/learning-to-live-together/?tx_browser_pi1%5BshowUid%5D=5278&cHash=54219839bb\n |title= Enfances en guerre. T\u00e9moignages d\u2019enfants sur la guerre |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://fr.unesco.org/ |publisher=}}</ref>  \n\n==Honours and awards==\n* 2002 : ''Premio Margherita Zoebeli'', \u00ab ''La bussola dell\u2019educazione'' \u00bb, Rimini, Italy\n* Ambassador of \u2018\u2019Children Refugees of the World\u2019\u2019\n* 1986 : Medal of the city of Bordeaux, France \n* 1981 : ''Monza Prize'' for the book \u00ab ''Living with an Autistic Child'' \u00bb, ''Biblioteca Italiana Per Ciechi'' \u00ab ''Regina Margherita'' \u00bb, Villa Reale, Monza, Italy\n* 1979 : ''First Prize'', ''International Rehabilitation Film Festival'' in the category \u00ab ''Mental Health Professional'' \u00bb for the film \u00ab ''Maison sans fen\u00eatres'' \u00bb, New York City, United States. \n* 1976: Hans-Prinzhorn Medal, German society of Psychophysiology and its applications (DGPA), Munich, Germany \n* 1970 : 3rd Prize, 6th Congress of the International society of psychopathology of expression  (SIPE), Istanbul, Turquie\n* 1970-1973 : President of the French Society of psychopathology of expression and Art \n* Croix de guerre 1939-1945, mentionned in dispatches by his division\n\n===Major works by Brauner===\n\n\nThe titles of the following publications have been translated from German or French into English and have been put in brackets.\n\n====Thesis====\n* (1946), Plan, organisation et r\u00e9sultats de la maison de r\u00e9\u00e9ducation de l'enfance d\u00e9linquante \u00e0 Kaiser-Ebersdorf, pr\u00e8s de Vienne, Autriche (Plan, Organization and Results of the Rehabilitation Center for Juvenile Offenders in Kaiserebersdorf near Vienna, Austria) (in French), complementary thesis, University of Paris La Sorbonne. \n* (1946), Les r\u00e9percussions psychiques de la guerre moderne sur l'enfance (The Psychic Repercussions of Modern War on Childhood) (in French), Higher doctorate (th\u00e8se d\u2019\u00c9tat), University of Paris La Sorbonne. \n* (1934), Der Unanimismus Jules Romains (The Unanimism of Jules Romains) (in German), Ph.D. thesis, University of Vienna.\n \n====Individual work====\n* (1997), Psy, es-tu l\u00e0 ? (Pdoc, are you in ?) (in French), Groupement de recherches pratiques pour l'enfance, ISBN 2-9511382-0-2\n* (1976), Les Enfants des Confins (in French),  Grasset, Paris, (ISBN 2-246-00359-8)\n* (1963), Titine et l'\u00e9ducation moderne. Une satire. (Titine and the modern education. A satire.) (in French), Groupement de recherches pratiques, Saint-Mand\u00e9.\n* (1956), Pour en faire des hommes. \u00c9tude sur le jeu et le langage chez les enfants \"inadapt\u00e9s sociaux\" (Study on play and language in \u00ab socially maladjusted \u00bb children), S.A.B.R.I., Paris.\n* (1951), Nos livres d'enfants ont menti ! (Our childhood books lied to us!) (in French),   S.A.B.R.I., Paris (preface by Henri Wallon).\n* (1946), Ces enfants ont v\u00e9cu la guerre (These Children Have Lived through the War) (in French), \u00c9ditions Sociales Fran\u00e7aises, Paris.\n* (1938) (dir. Alfred Brauner), The Spanish children and the International Brigades ; (translation in 5 languages : Les enfants espagnols et les Brigades internationales ; Die spanischen Kinder und die Internationalen Brigaden ; Spanelsk\u00e9 deti a Internacionalni Brig\u00e1dy), Comit\u00e9 Pro-Ni\u00f1os Espa\u00f1oles de las Brigadas Internacionales, Barcelona.\n\n====Collective work====\n* (2001),  L'expression dramatique chez l'enfant : Pris dans une guerre, handicap\u00e9 mental (The dramatic expression in children : Caught in the war, special need) (in French),  Cahiers du groupement de recherches pratiques pour l'enfance, Saint-Mand\u00e9.\n* (1994), L'accueil des enfants survivants, (The Welcoming of the Child Survivors) (in French), Cahiers du groupement de recherches pratiques pour l'enfance, Saint-Mand\u00e9.\n* (1991), J'ai dessin\u00e9 la guerre. Le dessin de l'enfant dans la guerre (I've drawn the war. Children's Drawings in the War) (in French), \u00c9ditions Scientifiques fran\u00e7aises, Paris, ISBN 2-7046-1378-8\n* (1986), L'Enfant d\u00e9r\u00e9el : histoire des autismes depuis les contes de f\u00e9es. Fictions litt\u00e9raires et r\u00e9alit\u00e9s cliniques (History of Autism since the Fairy Tales (in French), Privat, 1986, Toulouse, (ISBN 2-7089-7426-2)\n* (1982), Vivre avec un enfant autistique (Living with an Autistic child) (in French), Paris,  PUF, Paris, 2nd Ed., ISBN 2-13-037414-X\n* (1978), L'expression psychotique chez l'enfant (The psychotic expression in children) (in French),  PUF, Paris.\n* (1978), Vivre avec un enfant autistique (Living with an autistic child) (in French),  PUF,  (ISBN 2-13-037414-X)\nSpanish translation: Vivir con un nino autistico,  Paidos Iberica Ediciones S A, 1981 ISBN 8475091148\nItalian translation: Vivere con un bambino autistico,  Giunti Editore, 2007 ISBN 880904114\n* (1976), Dessins d'enfants de la guerre d'Espagne (Child drawings of the Spanish Civil War,  Groupement de Recherches Pratiques pour l'Enfance, Saint Mand\u00e9.\n\n====Academic articles (selection)====\n\n*\t(2000), (avec F. Brauner), Des guerres et des enfants handicap\u00e9s mentaux (Wars and Special Needs Children) (in French), Revue Europ\u00e9enne du Handicap Mental, p. 29-37.\n*\t(1999), Ces enfants ont v\u00e9cu la guerre, Les enfants de La Guette. Souvenirs et documents (1938-1945) (These children have lived through the war. La Guette children. Memories and documents (1938-1945) (in French), Centre de documentation juive contemporaine (CDJC), p. 57.\n*\t(1986), (avec F. Brauner), Pictures from an exhibition, Children in War: Drawings from the Afghan Refugee Camps (in English), (Preface by Sayed B. Majrooh), Central Asian Survey, Incidental Papers Series No 5, London,  Society for Central Asian Studies.\n*\t(1986), (avec F. Brauner), Children's Drawings and Nuclear War (in English), JAMA: The Journal of the American Medical Association 256(5) p.613-616 \n*\t(1985), (avec F. Brauner), Les enfants d\u00e9port\u00e9s pendant la deuxi\u00e8me guerre mondiale et leurs descendants (The deported children during the Second World War World and their descendants) (in French), Revue de Neuropsychiatrie de l'enfance et de l'adolescence, No 6, 1985, p. 251-259.\n \n====Bibliography====\n \n===In English=== \n* (2012), Duroux Rose, Milkovitch-Rioux Catherine, I have Drawn Pictures of the War. The Eye of Fran\u00e7oise and Alfred Brauner, Pu Blaise Pascal.\n\n===In French=== \n* (2013), Duroux Rose, Milkovitch-Rioux Catherine, Enfances en guerre. T\u00e9moignages d'enfants sur la guerre,  L'\u00c9quinoxe.\n* (1996), Pasteur Paul, Kreissler F\u00e9lix, Actes du Colloque. Les Autrichiens dans la R\u00e9sistance,  \u00e9d. Publications de l'Universit\u00e9 de Rouen, Centre d'\u00e9tudes et de recherches autrichiennes, Rouen.\n\n===In German=== \n\n* (2016), Sch\u00fctz Edgar, \u00d6sterreichische JournalistInnen und Publizistlnnen im Spanischen B\u00fcrgerkrieg 1936 - 1939,  LIT Verlag, Vienna.\n* (2003), Landauer Hans, Hackl Erich, Lexikon der \u00f6sterreichischen Spanienk\u00e4mpfer: 1936-1939, Verlag der Theodor-Kramer-Ges., Vienna, (ISBN 3901602186), S. 36. Internet access : \u00d6sterreicherInnen f\u00fcr Spaniens Freiheit 1936-1939: \u00ab Brauner, Alfred, Dr. \u00bb [archive], Dokumentationsarchiv des \u00f6sterreichischen Widerstandes.\n \n===Articles===\n* (2013), Poblaci\u00f3n F\u00e9lix, Los Brauner y los dibujos de los ni\u00f1os de las guerras (in Spanish), Cr\u00f3nica Popular. \n* (2010), Mouchenik Yoram, Les enfants dans la guerre. Entretien avec Alfred BRAUNER, L'Autre, (Vol. 11), p. 10-17 (in French). \n* (2006), Ripa Yannick, Naissance du dessin de guerre. Les \u00e9poux Brauner et les enfants de la guerre civile espagnole, dans Vingti\u00e8me Si\u00e8cle : Revue d'histoire, (No 89), p. 29-46 (in French). \n* (2004), Guillermo Casa\u00f1, Benic\u00e0ssim, hospital de las Brigadas Internacionales (Etapas Dumont y Ritterman), Aula militar, 2004 (in Spanish).\n* (2003), Perrier Edmond, \u00ab \u00c0 Alfred Brauner \u00bb, Sud/Nord, (No 18), p. 11-11 (in French). \n* (1947), Mauco Georges, \u00ab Brauner Alfred. - Ces enfants ont v\u00e9cu la guerre \u00bb, Population,  (Vol. 2), p. 383-384 (in French).\n\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brauner, Alfred}}\n[[Category:1910 births]]\n[[Category:2002 deaths]]\n[[Category:Child psychologists]]\n[[Category:French people of Austrian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:University of Paris alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Vienna alumni]]\n[[Category:Autism researchers]]\n[[Category:People from Vienna]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox academic\n| honorific_prefix   = Doctor of Philosophy \n| name               = Alfred Brauner\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| birth_name         = <!-- use only if different from full/othernames -->\n| birth_date         = {{birth date|1910|7|3|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Saint-Mand\u00e9]], [[Val-de-Marne]], [[France]]\n| death_date         = {{death date and age|2002|12|01|1910|07|03}}\n| death_place        = [[Paris]], [[France]]\n| death_cause        = \n| nationality        = Austrian \n| citizenship        = French \n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = \n| period             = \n| known_for          =  [[child psychology]] ; [[Autism]] ; [[Sociology of childhood]]\n| home_town          = \n| title              = \n| boards             = <!--board or similar positions extraneous to main occupation-->\n| spouse             = \n| partner            = \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| awards             = <!--notable national-level awards only-->\n| website            = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[University of Vienna]] ; [[University of Paris]] <!--will often consist of the linked name of the last-attended higher education institution-->\n| thesis_title       = \n| thesis_url         = \n| thesis_year        = \n| school_tradition   = \n| doctoral_advisor   = \n| academic_advisors  = \n| influences         = <!--must be referenced from a third-party source-->\n| era                = \n| discipline         = \n| sub_discipline     = <!--academic discipline specialist area \u2013 e.g. Sub-atomic research, 20th-century Danish specialist, Pauline research, Arcadian and Ugaritic specialist-->\n| workplaces         = <!--full-time positions only, not student positions-->\n| doctoral_students  = <!--only those with WP articles-->\n| notable_students   = <!--only those with WP articles-->\n| main_interests     = \n| notable_works      = \n| notable_ideas      = \n| influenced         = <!--must be referenced from a third-party source-->\n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Alfred Brauner''' (3 July 1910 - 1 December 2002) was an [[Austria|Austrian-born]] French [[scholar]], [[sociologist]], [[child psychologist]] and [[author]],   who was a volunteer in the [[International Brigades]] during the [[Spanish Civil War]]<ref name=\"\u00d6sterreicher\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.doew.at/erinnern/biographien/spanienarchiv-online/spanienfreiwillige-b/brauner-alfred-dr |title=\u00d6sterreicherInnen f\u00fcr Spaniens Freiheit 1936-1939 |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://www.doew.at/|publisher=Dokumentationsarchiv des \u00f6sterreichischen Widerstandes}}</ref> and a [[French Resistance]] member during [[Occupied France]]. He has devoted his life to educating refugee, displaced and maladjusted children, participating in the welcoming of Jewish child survivors of the [[Kristallnacht]] and of the [[Nazi concentration camps]] of [[Buchenwald]] and [[Auschwitz]] from 1939 to 1946<ref name=\"L'accueil\">{{cite book | author = Brauner Alfred, Brauner Fran\u00e7oise| title = L\u2019accueil des enfants survivants| page= | publisher = Cahiers du groupement de recherches pratiques pour l'enfance | year = 1994 | isbn = 978-0-7914-0453-9}}</ref>. An early writer on infantile autism,  he also pioneered the analysis of children\u2019s drawings in war, creating from 1938 the first collection of drawing-testimonials<ref name=dessin\u00e9>{{cite book | author = Brauner Alfred, Fran\u00e7oise| title = J\u2019ai dessin\u00e9 la guerre. Le dessin de l'enfant dans la guerre | page= | publisher = Elsevier| year = 1991 | isbn = 2-7046-1378-8}}</ref> to offer a unique perspective of the major conflicts of the [[20th century]] through the eyes of children.<ref name=\"Bio\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Brauner | first1 = Alfred | authorlink = Alfred Brauner| title = Biographie du docteur Fran\u00e7oise Brauner| doi = 10.3917/sn.018.0167.| journal = Sud/Nord| volume = 18 | issue = 1 | pages = 167\u201373| year = 2003 | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>.\n \n==Background in Austria and education==\n \nBorn in 1910 in [[Saint-Mand\u00e9]] to [[Austro-Hungarian]] parents spending two years in [[France]] for professional reasons, Alfred Brauner comes from a prestigious Viennese family. <ref name=\" Brauner Claude-Michel\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.enfance-violence-exil.net/fichiers_sgc/BRAUNER.pdf |title=Alfred et Fran\u00e7oise Brauner par leur fils |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= publisher=}}</ref>  In Vienna, his family held private classical music concerts at the [[Palais Esterh\u00e1zy]], where [[Sigmund Freud]] was invited. <ref name==\"Cyrulnik >{{cite book | author =Cyrulnik Boris | title = De Chair et d'\u00e2me | page= 229 | publisher = \u00c9ditions Odile Jacob | year = 2006  | isbn = }}</ref><ref name=\"Brauner Claude-Michel \" /> In his childhood, he experienced himself the repercussions of the war and witnessed his father leaving for the [[First World War]] to serve in the Austro-Hungarian army. <ref name=\"L'accueil\"/> To save him from the epidemics, during the First World War, his parents sent him to a family in [[Moravia]]. <ref name=\"L'accueil\"/> He defended his doctoral thesis in philosophy at the [[University of Vienna]] in 1934, entitled \"The Unanimism of Jules Romains,\" a correspondence starting between the young Viennese doctoral student and [[Jules Romains]]. <ref name=\"Yannick Ripa\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Ripa | first1 = Yannick | authorlink = Yannick Ripa| title = Naissance du dessin de guerre. Les \u00e9poux Brauner et les enfants de la guerre civile espagnole | doi = 10.3917/ving.089.0029 | journal = Vingti\u00e8me Si\u00e8cle. Revue d\u2019Histoire| volume = 89 | issue = 1 | pages = 29\u201346| year = 2006 | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>. Alfred served in the French army from 1939 and was decorated with the [[Croix de Guerre 1939-1945]]. <ref name=\"\u00c0 Alfred Brauner \">{{Cite journal | last1 = Perrier | first1 = Edmond | authorlink = Edmond Perrier| title = \u00c0 Alfred Brauner| doi =  | journal = Sud/ Nord| volume = 18  | issue = 1  | pages = 11-11 | year = 2003 | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref> In 1946, he defended a thesis at the [[University of Paris]] on \u201cThe Psychic Repercussions of Modern War on Childhood\"<ref name=\"Yannick Ripa\"/> and the same year presented a complementary thesis entitled \"Plan, Organization and Results of the Rehabilitation Center for Juvenile Offenders in Kaiserebersdorf near Vienna (Austria). \" His younger brother William emigrated to the [[United States]] before the beginning of the [[Second World War]] and died on October 6, 1948 in the [[1948 Georgia USAF Boeing B-29 crash]], which resulted in the US court case [[United States v. Reynolds]]. <ref name=\"LA Times\">{{Cite journal | last1 =Siegel  | first1 =Barry  | authorlink = | title = A Daughter Discovers What Really Happened | doi = | journal = Los Angeles Times | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2004  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref><ref name=\"LA\">{{Cite journal | last1 =Barry  | first1 = Siegel  | authorlink = | title = How the Death of Judy\u2019s Father Made America More Secretive | doi = | journal = Los Angeles Times | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2004  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref><ref name=\"legal affairs\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Freedman  | first1 = Michael  | authorlink = | title = Daughters of the Cold War. Three women sue the Air Force for covering up the deaths of their fathers in a 1948 test flight. | doi = | journal = Legal Affairs | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2004  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\n\nAlfred began his professional activity as an educator in a rehabilitation center for juvenile offenders at Kaiserebersdorf in [[Vienna]] from 1928 to 1933. <ref name=\"Mintec\">{{Cite web|url= https://docplayer.fr/80750089-Fonds-brauner-repertoire-numerique-alfred-et-francoise-brauner.html |title= FONDS BRAUNER:REPERTOIRE NUMERIQUE |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= publisher=' }}</ref> During the [[Spanish Civil War]], Alfred Brauner volunteered in the [[International Brigades]] and was placed at the head of a committee to help evacuees or refugees, because of his previous experience with at-risk youth.<ref name=\"L'accueil\"/><ref name=\"\u00d6sterreicher\"/><ref name=\"Barcelona\">{{Cite web|url=http://sidbrint.ub.edu/en/content/brauner-alfred |title= DADES DEL BRIGADISTA. BRAUNER, Alfred |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= http://sidbrint.ub.edu/en publisher=Barcelona University}}</ref><ref name=\"Sugarman\">{{Cite web|url= https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/jsource/History/spanjews.pdf |title= Against Fascism - Jews who served in The International Brigade in the Spanish Civil War |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org publisher=Jewish Virtual Library}}</ref> It is a home for children evacuated from Madrid and Asturias after the [[bombing of Guernica]], the goal being to help the Spanish children of Republican territories, in the country and in the combat zone.<ref name=\"L'accueil\"/><ref name=thesis>{{cite book | author =Brauner Alfred | title =The Psychic Repercussions of Modern War on Childhood| page= | publisher =University of Paris La Sorbonne | year = 1946  | isbn = }}</ref> Finally, Alfred returned to France after the defeat of the [[Spanish Republic]].<ref name=\"\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Requeno Gallego | first1 = Manuel   | last2 = Sep\u00falveda Losa     | first2 = Rosa Mar\u00eda | authorlink = | title = La sanidad en las Brigadas Internacionales | doi = | journal = Ediciones de la Universidad de Castilla-La Mancha | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2006  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>><ref name=\"Lefebvre\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Lefebvre  | first1 = Michel  | last2 = Latorre | first2 = Marga | authorlink = | title = Las brigadas internacionales : im\u00e1genes recuperadas | doi = | journal = Lunwerg Editores | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2003  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>\n\nIn 1938, Alfred Brauner and his wife Fritzi discovered the trauma of child victims of war after receiving a set of drawings from a class in Barcelona. These were, in addition to Catalan schoolchildren who were fortunate enough to stay in their school, refugees from Madrid who had witnessed tragic events. The Brauners made a pedo-psychiatric analysis of the child's drawing, a privileged mode of graphic expression of the young child, highlighting what seems to them characteristic of the child's drawing in the war, taking notes, creating medical records and questionnaires. Drawings and writings of children of the Spanish War were the result of a contest organized by Alfred Brauner among the children of Barcelona in 1938 on three themes: \"My life Before the War\", \"What I Saw from the War\" and \"How I See My Life after the War\". <ref name=thesis/>. It was then the beginning of their work on \"children who have lived through the war.\" 4000 drawings of refugee children and numerous essays were collected in Spain, which later, along with other drawings of children in war, offered a unique testimony of the conflicts of the 20th century through the eyes of children. <ref name=\"\">{{Cite journal | last1 =Ibarz Serrat  | first1 = Virgilio  | authorlink = | title = Los dibujos infantiles de la guerra 1937-1938: el caso de la ni\u00f1a de Ballobar | doi = | journal = Diario del AltoArag\u00f3n | volume =  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2009  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>. Their project to publish drawings and testimonies of children in war received the support of [[Ilya Ehrenburg]] and [[Romain Rolland]] who \"regarded this collection as of considerable educational, historical and human interest.\" <ref name=\"Yannick Ripa\"/>\n \nIn 1939, Alfred Brauner welcomed 130 Jewish children from the Palatinate, Berlin and Austria, <ref name=\"L'accueil\"/> survivors of the [[Kristallnacht]] at La Guette, a French castle owned by the Rothschild family and made available by [[Baroness Germaine de Rothschild]]. <ref name=\"La Guette\">{{Cite web|url= http://www.ajpn.org/sauvetage-Chateau-de-la-Guette-245.html |title= Ch\u00e2teau de la Guette durant la Seconde Guerre mondiale (WWII) |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= http://www.ajpn.org/index.php | publisher= }}</ref><ref name=\"\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Lochy  | first1 = Emilie | authorlink = | title = Extrait de l'ouvrage : Enfances en guerre - T\u00e9moignages d'enfants sur la guerre | doi = | journal = Le Cercle Psy | volume = 12  | issue =  | pages = | year = 2014 | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref>. Alfred\u2019s  intention was to analyze the problems posed in working with children traumatized by their experiences and by separation from their families, with the aim of adapting them to a new life and preparing them for integration into France. <ref name=\"L'accueil\"/> He then described this educational experience in his state thesis, defended in 1946, entitled \"The Psychic Repercussions of Modern War on Childhood.\" <ref name=thesis/>\n \nFrom January 1941, Alfred Brauner entered the [[French Resistance]] and welcomed the [[Austrian resistance]]\u2019s leadership in his [[Rue Bonaparte]] apartment in [[Paris]].<ref name=\"Resistance\">{{Cite journal | last1 = Brauner  | first1 = Fran\u00e7oise Erna  | authorlink = | title = L'an\u00e9antissement de deux r\u00e9seaux de la r\u00e9sistance | doi = 10.3917/sn.018.0034\n | journal = Sud/Nord | volume = 18  | issue = 1  | pages = 34-48 | year = 2003  | jstor =| pmid = | pmc = }}</ref><ref name=\"Bio\"/> With members of the [[\u00d6sterreichische Freiheitsfront]] arriving every morning at a specific time, Alfred Brauner decided to open a German Language course as a cover from [[Gestapo]]. <ref name=\"Resistance\"/> In 1945, he helped welcoming and educating 444 surviving boys from the [[Auschwitz]] and [[Buchenwald]] [[concentration camps]], in the scope of the [[Oeuvre de Secours aux Enfants]] (O.S.E.) in [[Ecouis]], [[France]]. This welcoming of Buchenwald's child survivors in children's homes inspired the script of the film [[Nina\u2019s House]],<ref name=\" \">{{Cite web|url= https://jeudisducinema.be/La-maison-de-Nina |title= La maison de Nina |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://jeudisducinema.be/ | publisher=Les jeudis du cinema }}</ref> as well as the documentary [[The Boys of Buchenwald]].\n \nIn 1950, Alfred Brauner created the \"Practical Research for Children,\" which brings together professionals of childhood in order to develop medico-pedagogical methods intended for the education of children with mental disabilities.<ref name=\"Mintec\"/>. In 1955, he founded a day hospital for mentally and physically handicapped children located in the center of Paris, then transferred to Saint-Mand\u00e9, and worked on the rehabilitation of these children, giving priority to their education. <ref name=\"Bio\"/> Alfred Brauner was the ambassador of the association \"Children Refugees of the World,\" as well as the only non-physician president of the Society of Expression Psychopathology and Art Therapy. <ref name=\"SFPE\">{{Cite web|url= https://www.sfpe-art-therapie.fr/Quelques-dates-qui-marquent-les-avancees-sur-trois-voies-paralleles_a34.html |title= Quelques dates qui marquent les avanc\u00e9es sur trois voies parall\u00e8les. La voie hexagonale |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://www.sfpe-art-therapie.fr/ | publisher=SFPE}}</ref><ref name=\"BNF\">{{Cite web|url= https://catalogue.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb118938323 |title= Notice de personne. Brauner, Alfred (1910-2002) |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://catalogue.bnf.fr/index.do | publisher=Biblioth\u00e8que nationale de France}}</ref> He was awarded the [[Hans Prinzhorn]] medal of the \"German-speaking Society for the Psychopathology of Expression\" in 1976. <ref name=\"Prinzhorn\">{{Cite web|url= https://www.dgpa.org/prinzhorn.php?m=6 |title= Preistr\u00e4ger der Hans Prinzhorn Medaille |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://www.dgpa.org/  |publisher=''Deutschsprachige Gesellschaft\nf\u00fcr Kunst & Psychopathologie des Ausdrucks e.V.''}}</ref> In 1986, [[Jacques Chaban-Delmas]] offered him the medal of the city of [[Bordeaux]]. <ref name=\" Brauner Claude-Michel\"/>\n \nOver the course of their career, the Brauners have analyzed children's drawings collected from around the world from children in about 20 countries at war, including the Boer War, the First World War, the Spanish War, Nazi Germany, Poland 1939, concentration camps, Hiroshima-Nagasaki, Polisario, the Israeli-Palestinian Conflict, the Lebanon War, the Algerian War, the Western Sahara War, El Salvador, Afghanistan, the Gulf War, Bosnia, and Chechnya. <ref name=dessin\u00e9/>.\n \nFrom 18 January to 10 February 1999, at the [[UNESCO]] headquarters in [[Paris]], an  exhibition was held with more than 200 drawings of children who lived through  war. Entitled \"I\u2019ve Drawn the War. A Century of Drawings of Children in Wars (1900-1999), under the high sponsorship and under the patronage of [[Simone Veil]], these drawings-testimonials belonging to the Brauner collection revealed the impact of the extreme violence of war for the child.<ref name=\"Enfances en guerre\">{{Cite web|url= https://magasindesenfants.hypotheses.org/2215\n |title= Enfances en guerre. T\u00e9moignages d\u2019enfants sur la guerre |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= |publisher=Open Edition}}</ref> This exhibition, which was considered part of the \"World Heritage,\" was then shown in Hiroshima, Jerusalem, Budapest, Vienna and more than 40 cities in Germany.  From 7 to 9 December 2011, a tribute to the 100th anniversary of the birth of the Brauners (1911-2011) was organized at UNESCO Headquarters, with the organization of an international colloquium entitled '' Childhood in War. Testimonies from Children about War.''<ref name=\"UNESCO \">{{Cite web|url= http://www.unesco.org/new/fr/unesco/events/learning-to-live-together/?tx_browser_pi1%5BshowUid%5D=5278&cHash=54219839bb\n |title= Enfances en guerre. T\u00e9moignages d\u2019enfants sur la guerre |accessdate=21 April 2020 |website= https://fr.unesco.org/ |publisher=}}</ref>  \n\n==Honours and awards==\n* 2002 : ''Premio Margherita Zoebeli'', \u00ab ''La bussola dell\u2019educazione'' \u00bb, Rimini, Italy\n* Ambassador of \u2018\u2019Children Refugees of the World\u2019\u2019\n* (1986) : Medal of the city of Bordeaux, France \n* 1981 : ''Monza Prize'' for the book \u00ab ''Living with an Autistic Child'' \u00bb, ''Biblioteca Italiana Per Ciechi'' \u00ab ''Regina Margherita'' \u00bb, Villa Reale, Monza, Italy\n* 1979 : ''First Prize'', ''International Rehabilitation Film Festival'' in the category \u00ab ''Mental Health Professional'' \u00bb for the film \u00ab ''Maison sans fen\u00eatres'' \u00bb, New York City, United States. \n* 1976: Hans-Prinzhorn Medal, German society of Psychophysiology and its applications (DGPA), Munich, Germany \n* 1970 : 3rd Prize, 6th Congress of the International society of psychopathology of expression  (SIPE), Istanbul, Turquie\n* 1970-1973 : President of the French Society of psychopathology of expression and Art \n* Croix de guerre 1939-1945, mentionned in dispatches by his division\n\n===Major works by Brauner===\n\n\nThe titles of the following publications have been translated from German or French into English and have been put in brackets.\n\n====Thesis====\n* (1946), Plan, organisation et r\u00e9sultats de la maison de r\u00e9\u00e9ducation de l'enfance d\u00e9linquante \u00e0 Kaiser-Ebersdorf, pr\u00e8s de Vienne, Autriche (Plan, Organization and Results of the Rehabilitation Center for Juvenile Offenders in Kaiserebersdorf near Vienna, Austria) (in French), complementary thesis, University of Paris La Sorbonne. \n* (1946), Les r\u00e9percussions psychiques de la guerre moderne sur l'enfance (The Psychic Repercussions of Modern War on Childhood) (in French), Higher doctorate (th\u00e8se d\u2019\u00c9tat), University of Paris La Sorbonne. \n* (1934), Der Unanimismus Jules Romains (The Unanimism of Jules Romains) (in German), Ph.D. thesis, University of Vienna.\n \n====Individual work====\n* (1997), Psy, es-tu l\u00e0 ? (Pdoc, are you in ?) (in French), Groupement de recherches pratiques pour l'enfance, ISBN 2-9511382-0-2\n* (1976), Les Enfants des Confins (in French),  Grasset, Paris, (ISBN 2-246-00359-8)\n* (1963), Titine et l'\u00e9ducation moderne. Une satire. (Titine and the modern education. A satire.) (in French), Groupement de recherches pratiques, Saint-Mand\u00e9.\n* (1956), Pour en faire des hommes. \u00c9tude sur le jeu et le langage chez les enfants \"inadapt\u00e9s sociaux\" (Study on play and language in \u00ab socially maladjusted \u00bb children), S.A.B.R.I., Paris.\n* (1951), Nos livres d'enfants ont menti ! (Our childhood books lied to us!) (in French),   S.A.B.R.I., Paris (preface by Henri Wallon).\n* (1946), Ces enfants ont v\u00e9cu la guerre (These Children Have Lived through the War) (in French), \u00c9ditions Sociales Fran\u00e7aises, Paris.\n* (1938) (dir. Alfred Brauner), The Spanish children and the International Brigades ; (translation in 5 languages : Les enfants espagnols et les Brigades internationales ; Die spanischen Kinder und die Internationalen Brigaden ; Spanelsk\u00e9 deti a Internacionalni Brig\u00e1dy), Comit\u00e9 Pro-Ni\u00f1os Espa\u00f1oles de las Brigadas Internacionales, Barcelona.\n\n====Collective work====\n* (2001),  L'expression dramatique chez l'enfant : Pris dans une guerre, handicap\u00e9 mental (The dramatic expression in children : Caught in the war, special need) (in French),  Cahiers du groupement de recherches pratiques pour l'enfance, Saint-Mand\u00e9.\n* (1994), L'accueil des enfants survivants, (The Welcoming of the Child Survivors) (in French), Cahiers du groupement de recherches pratiques pour l'enfance, Saint-Mand\u00e9.\n* (1991), J'ai dessin\u00e9 la guerre. Le dessin de l'enfant dans la guerre (I've drawn the war. Children's Drawings in the War) (in French), \u00c9ditions Scientifiques fran\u00e7aises, Paris, ISBN 2-7046-1378-8\n* (1986), L'Enfant d\u00e9r\u00e9el : histoire des autismes depuis les contes de f\u00e9es. Fictions litt\u00e9raires et r\u00e9alit\u00e9s cliniques (History of Autism since the Fairy Tales (in French), Privat, 1986, Toulouse, (ISBN 2-7089-7426-2)\n* (1982), Vivre avec un enfant autistique (Living with an Autistic child) (in French), Paris,  PUF, Paris, 2nd Ed., ISBN 2-13-037414-X\n* (1978), L'expression psychotique chez l'enfant (The psychotic expression in children) (in French),  PUF, Paris.\n* (1978), Vivre avec un enfant autistique (Living with an autistic child) (in French),  PUF,  (ISBN 2-13-037414-X)\nSpanish translation: Vivir con un nino autistico,  Paidos Iberica Ediciones S A, 1981 ISBN 8475091148\nItalian translation: Vivere con un bambino autistico,  Giunti Editore, 2007 ISBN 880904114\n* (1976), Dessins d'enfants de la guerre d'Espagne (Child drawings of the Spanish Civil War,  Groupement de Recherches Pratiques pour l'Enfance, Saint Mand\u00e9.\n\n====Academic articles (selection)====\n\n*\t(2000), (avec F. Brauner), Des guerres et des enfants handicap\u00e9s mentaux (Wars and Special Needs Children) (in French), Revue Europ\u00e9enne du Handicap Mental, p. 29-37.\n*\t(1999), Ces enfants ont v\u00e9cu la guerre, Les enfants de La Guette. Souvenirs et documents (1938-1945) (These children have lived through the war. La Guette children. Memories and documents (1938-1945) (in French), Centre de documentation juive contemporaine (CDJC), p. 57.\n*\t(1986), (avec F. Brauner), Pictures from an exhibition, Children in War: Drawings from the Afghan Refugee Camps (in English), (Preface by Sayed B. Majrooh), Central Asian Survey, Incidental Papers Series No 5, London,  Society for Central Asian Studies.\n*\t(1986), (avec F. Brauner), Children's Drawings and Nuclear War (in English), JAMA: The Journal of the American Medical Association 256(5) p.613-616 \n*\t(1985), (avec F. Brauner), Les enfants d\u00e9port\u00e9s pendant la deuxi\u00e8me guerre mondiale et leurs descendants (The deported children during the Second World War World and their descendants) (in French), Revue de Neuropsychiatrie de l'enfance et de l'adolescence, No 6, 1985, p. 251-259.\n \n====Bibliography====\n \n===In English=== \n* (2012), Duroux Rose, Milkovitch-Rioux Catherine, I have Drawn Pictures of the War. The Eye of Fran\u00e7oise and Alfred Brauner, Pu Blaise Pascal.\n\n===In French=== \n* (2013), Duroux Rose, Milkovitch-Rioux Catherine, Enfances en guerre. T\u00e9moignages d'enfants sur la guerre,  L'\u00c9quinoxe.\n* (1996), Pasteur Paul, Kreissler F\u00e9lix, Actes du Colloque. Les Autrichiens dans la R\u00e9sistance,  \u00e9d. Publications de l'Universit\u00e9 de Rouen, Centre d'\u00e9tudes et de recherches autrichiennes, Rouen.\n\n===In German=== \n\n* (2016), Sch\u00fctz Edgar, \u00d6sterreichische JournalistInnen und Publizistlnnen im Spanischen B\u00fcrgerkrieg 1936 - 1939,  LIT Verlag, Vienna.\n* (2003), Landauer Hans, Hackl Erich, Lexikon der \u00f6sterreichischen Spanienk\u00e4mpfer: 1936-1939, Verlag der Theodor-Kramer-Ges., Vienna, (ISBN 3901602186), S. 36. Internet access : \u00d6sterreicherInnen f\u00fcr Spaniens Freiheit 1936-1939: \u00ab Brauner, Alfred, Dr. \u00bb [archive], Dokumentationsarchiv des \u00f6sterreichischen Widerstandes.\n \n===Articles===\n* (2013), Poblaci\u00f3n F\u00e9lix, Los Brauner y los dibujos de los ni\u00f1os de las guerras (in Spanish), Cr\u00f3nica Popular. \n* (2010), Mouchenik Yoram, Les enfants dans la guerre. Entretien avec Alfred BRAUNER, L'Autre, (Vol. 11), p. 10-17 (in French). \n* (2006), Ripa Yannick, Naissance du dessin de guerre. Les \u00e9poux Brauner et les enfants de la guerre civile espagnole, dans Vingti\u00e8me Si\u00e8cle : Revue d'histoire, (No 89), p. 29-46 (in French). \n* (2004), Guillermo Casa\u00f1, Benic\u00e0ssim, hospital de las Brigadas Internacionales (Etapas Dumont y Ritterman), Aula militar, 2004 (in Spanish).\n* (2003), Perrier Edmond, \u00ab \u00c0 Alfred Brauner \u00bb, Sud/Nord, (No 18), p. 11-11 (in French). \n* (1947), Mauco Georges, \u00ab Brauner Alfred. - Ces enfants ont v\u00e9cu la guerre \u00bb, Population,  (Vol. 2), p. 383-384 (in French).\n\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brauner, Alfred}}\n[[Category:1910 births]]\n[[Category:2002 deaths]]\n[[Category:Child psychologists]]\n[[Category:French people of Austrian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:University of Paris alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Vienna alumni]]\n[[Category:Autism researchers]]\n[[Category:People from Vienna]]\n", "name_user": "BerlinFR2503", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alfred_Brauner"}
{"title_page": "Computer security conference", "text_new": "A '''computer security conference''' is a [[Convention (meeting)|convention]] for individuals involved in [[computer security]]. They generally serve as meeting places for [[System administrator|system]] and [[network administrator]]s, [[hacker (computer security)|hacker]]s, and computer security experts.\n\n==Events==\n[[File:Michael Lynn Black Hat Briefing Las Vegas 2005.jpg|thumb|Michael Lynn, a keynote speaker at [[Black Hat Briefings]] 2005]]\nCommon activities at hacker conventions may include:\n* Presentations from keynote speakers or panels. Common topics include [[Social engineering (security)|social engineering]], [[lockpicking]], [[penetration testing]], and hacking tools.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagocon.com/content/view/33/12}}{{dead link|date=April 2013 | title=Unknown}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sxconference.com |title=SX - Security Exchange '12 |publisher=M.Tech Products |year=2012 |accessdate=2013-04-05 }}</ref>\n* Hands-on activities and competitions such as [[Capture the flag#Computer security|capture the flag]] (CTF). \n* \"Boot camps\" offering training and certification in Information Technology.<ref>[http://www.chicagocon.com/content/view/97/7] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081120004825/http://www.chicagocon.com/content/view/97/7 |date=November 20, 2008 }}</ref>\n\n===List of general computer security conferences===\nGeneral security conferences might be held by non-profit/not-for-profit/for-profit professional associations, individuals or informal group of individuals, or by security product vendor companies.\n[[File:Haroon meer keynote speaker at nullcon 2018.jpg|alt=|thumb|Haroon Meer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nullcon.net/website/goa-2018/speakers/haroon-meer.php|title=Haroon Meer|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>, a keynote speaker at nullcon 2018]]\n\n<!-- PLEASE RESPECT ALPHABETICAL ORDER -->\n* 44Con <ref>{{cite web|url=https://44con.com/ |title=44Con Website |publisher=44Con |date= |accessdate=2019-01-14}}</ref> An Infosec conference and training event that occurs annually in London, UK.\n* [[Association for Computing Machinery|ACM]]-CCS (Conferences on Computer and Communications Security),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sigsac.org/ccs.html |title=Acm Ccs |publisher=Sigsac.org |date=2012-01-23 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> security conference held since 1993.\n* [[ACSAC]], Annual Computer Security Applications Conference<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acsac.org |title=Security Conference, Security Training & Security Networking - ACSAC 2013 |publisher=ACSAC |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> - oldest information security ''conference'' held annually.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acsac.org/archive |title=Past ACSACs - Annual Computer Security Applications Conference |publisher=ACSAC |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* ASIA or the Annual Symposium on Information Assurance<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.albany.edu/iasymposium |title=Annual Symposium on Information Assurance (ASIA) |publisher=Albany.edu |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> that serves as the academic track for the [[New York (state)|New York]] State Cyber Security Conference,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cscic.state.ny.us/security/conferences |title=NYS Division of Homeland Security & Emergency Services - OCS |publisher=Cscic.state.ny.us |date=2013-02-21 |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110221112525/http://www.cscic.state.ny.us/security/conferences/ |archive-date=2011-02-21 |url-status=dead }}</ref> an annual information security conference held in [[Albany, NY]] usually for two days during June targeted at academic, government, and industry participants.\n* [[Black Hat Briefings|Black Hat]], a series of conferences held annually in different cities around the world. Black Hat USA, held in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]] immediately before [[DEF CON (convention)|DEF CON]], is one of the largest [[computer security]] events in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blackhat.com |title=Black Hat |publisher=Black Hat |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* \n* [[BlueHat]] Conference, a twice a year, invitation-only [[Microsoft]] security conference aimed at bringing Microsoft security professionals and external security researchers together.<ref name=\"microsoft.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.microsoft.com/technet/security/bluehat/default.mspx |title=Bluehat Security Briefings |publisher=Microsoft.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref name=\"news.cnet.com\">{{cite news|url=http://news.cnet.com/Microsoft-meets-the-hackers/2009-1002_3-5747813.html |title=Microsoft meets the hackers |publisher=CNET News |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref name=\"technet.microsoft.com\">{{cite web|url=https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/security/cc261637.aspx |title=Bluehat Security Briefings |publisher=Technet.microsoft.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Brucon]], yearly conference, previously held in [[Brussels]], since 2012 it is held in [[Ghent]]. Lasting 2 days, and preceded by a training.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brucon.org|accessdate=27 April 2015 | title=BruconTraining}}</ref>\n* [[CanSecWest]], in [[Vancouver]]  is held at the end of March and hosts the [[Pwn2Own]] hacking contest.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cansecwest.com |title=CanSecWest Applied Security Conference: Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada |publisher=Cansecwest.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Naraine |first=Ryan |url=http://www.zdnet.com/blog/security/cansecwest-pwn2own-hacker-challenge-gets-a-105000-makeover/10182 |title=CanSecWest Pwn2Own hacker challenge gets a $105,000 makeover |publisher=ZDNet |date=2012-01-23 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Mills |first=Elinor |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-27080_3-20001126-245.html |title=iPhone, Safari, IE 8, Firefox hacked in CanSecWest contest |publisher=CNET News |date=2010-03-24 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* CSS - International Conference on Cryptography and Security System<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.css.umcs.lublin.pl |title=css.umcs.lublin.pl |publisher=css.umcs.lublin.pl |date= |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref> in Poland.\n* [[DeepSec]], in [[Vienna]]  covers many security aspects of computing and electronic communications as well as security management and social aspects. DeepSec is visited by a broad international audience, academics, researchers, vendors, finance, public administration etc. (2 days trainings, 2 days conference).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ethicalhacker.net/component/option,com_smf/Itemid,54/topic,9163.0 |title=DeepSec 2012 |publisher=The Ethical Hacker Network |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121030222352/http://www.ethicalhacker.net/component/option,com_smf/Itemid,54/topic,9163.0/ |archive-date=2012-10-30 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Presentations are published on Vimeo and YouTube.\n* [[Department of Defense Cyber Crime Center#Defense Cyber Crime Conference|Department of Defense Cyber Crime Conference]], an annual conference that focuses on the computer security needs of the United States federal government, military, and defense contractors.\n* FSec - Croatian annual security conference held at the Faculty of organization and informatics in [[Vara\u017edin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fsec.foi.hr |title=FSec |publisher=FSec |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[GreHack.fr]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://grehack.fr |title=grehack.fr |publisher=grehack.fr |date=2013-11-15 |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref> an annual conference held in [[Grenoble]],. Speakers from academia, industry. Both offensive and defensive security.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grehack.fr |title=Security, Ethical Hacking conference and Capture The Flag (CTF) in Grenoble |publisher=GreHack |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Hack.lu]], an annual conference held in [[Luxembourg]]\n* [[Hacker Halted]], Presented by [[EC-Council]], the objective of the global series of Hacker Halted conferences is to raise international awareness towards increased education and ethics in IT Security.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hackerhalted.com |title=Hacker Halted 2012 |publisher=Hackerhalted.com |date=2012-09-21 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[HackinParis]], Is an annual event organized by [[SYSDREAM]]. The program includes IT security, industrial espionage, penetration testing, physical security, social engineering, forensics, malware analysis techniques and countermeasures.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hackinparis.com |title=Hack in Paris 2019 |publisher=hackinparis.com |date=2019-01-10 |accessdate=2019-01-15}}</ref>\n*[https://www.hack-it-n.com/ HACK-IT-N] is a cybersecurity conference that deals with current issues and offensive and defensive techniques of the moment: hacking, cyber-espionage, cyber-surveillance etc. It's held in Bordeaux at the end of each year and organized by [https://tehtris.com/en/home/ TEHTRIS] and the [https://enseirb-matmeca.bordeaux-inp.fr/fr ENSEIRB-MATMECA] engineering school. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hack-it-n.com/|title=HACK-IT-N|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* [[Hackito Ergo Sum]], Security conference pertaining to research topics, with attendees and speakers from both the industry, the offensive side and the academic circles, held in Paris every April.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hackitoergosum.org |title=Hackito Ergo Sum 2013 |publisher=Hackitoergosum.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[HITBSecConf / Hack In The Box]], deep-knowledge security conference held in Malaysia and the Netherlands.<ref>[http://www.conference.hitb.org conference.hitb.org] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140625153121/http://conference.hitb.org/ |date=2014-06-25 }}</ref>\n* [[ICISSP]]  International Conference on Information Systems Security and Privacy,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.icissp.org |title=ICISSP International Conference on Information Systems Security and Privacy}}</ref> \n* [[IEEE]] Symposium on Security and Privacy,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ieee-security.org/TC/SP-Index.html |title=IEEE Symposium on Security and Privacy |publisher=Ieee-security.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> top-tier privacy & security conference.\n* IIA/ISACA Chicago IT Hacking and Cybersecurity Conference, a regional, two-day event that brings together executives and professionals in audit, IT, and risk management functions to hear current trends and first-hand knowledge from subject matter experts. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://chapters.theiia.org/chicago/Events/Pages/IIA-ISACA-6th-Annual-IT-Hacking-n-Cybersecurity-Conference.aspx |title=6th Annual IIA/ISACA Chicago IT Hacking and Cybersecurity Conference |year=2019 }}</ref> \n* [[INFWARCON]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://infowarcon.com/ |title=infowarcon.com |publisher=infowarcon.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref> Beyond Information Warfare - Offensive Cyber Weapons and Technologies Training Congress.\n* IP EXPO Europe, held annually at London's ExCeL Centre\n* IP EXPO Nordic, held annually at Stockholm's Waterfront Congress Centre\n* IWSECC International Workshop on Security Engineering for Cloud Computing in conjunction with the 14th International Conference on Availability, Reliability and Security (ARES \u2013 http://www.ares-conference.eu)\n* LeetCon, IT-Security-Convention in Hannover (Germany), frequently October or November every Year. Talks about IT-Security, IoT, Industry 4.0 and more.\n* NDSS (Network & Distributed System Security Symposium),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.internetsociety.org/events/ndss-symposium |title=NDSS Network & Distributed System Security Symposium |publisher=Internet Society |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> annual security conference from Internet Society.\n* NSPW (New Security Paradigms Workshop),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nspw.org |title=Introduction &#124; New Security Paradigms Workshop |publisher=Nspw.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> a workshop with new ideas in security.\n* nullcon Security Conference is an annual security event held in Goa, India.<ref name=\"nulcon.net\">{{cite web|url=http://nullcon.net |title=International Security Conference |publisher=nullcon |date=2013-03-02 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref name=\"zeenews.india.com\">{{cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/net-news/cyber-experts-show-vulnerability-of-gsm-networks_759318.html |title=Cyber experts show vulnerability of GSM networks |publisher=Zeenews.india.com |date=2012-02-19 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[OWASP|Open Web Application Security Project (OWASP)]], Focuses on web application security.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appsecusa.org |title=Appsec USA 2013 |publisher=OWASP |year=2013 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[REcon]] REcon is a computer security conference with a focus on reverse engineering and advanced exploitation techniques.\n* [[RSA Conference|RSA Security Conference]], Cryptography and information security-related conference held annually in the San Francisco Bay Area.\n* [[RuhrSec]], annual non-profit security conference at the Ruhr University Bochum.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ruhrsec.de/ |title=RuhrSec Conference |publisher=Hackmanit |year=2017 |accessdate=2017-01-05}}</ref>\n* [[S4:SCADA Security Scientific Symposium]], Security conference pertaining to SCADA held annually by Digital Bond, usually in [[Miami]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalbond.com/index.php/events |title=ICS Security Event Calendar |publisher=Digitalbond.com |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101228203154/http://www.digitalbond.com/index.php/events/ |archive-date=2010-12-28 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* SecurIT 2012, International Conference on Security of [[Internet of Things]] held in mid of August at [[Amrita Vishwa Vidyapeetham]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.securit.ws |title=SecurIT 2012 - Cyber Security conference on IoT |publisher=Securit.ws |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* SecureWorld Expo, a series of IT Security conferences offering education, CPE training opportunities, and networking of security leaders, experts, senior executives, and policy makers who shape the face of security.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.secureworldexpo.com |title=SecureWorld Conferences |publisher=Seguro Group |work=SecureWorld Post |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[SIN ACM]], or the International Conference on Security of Information and Networks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sinconf.org |title= the International Conference on Security of Information and Networks (SINCONF)}}</ref>\n* [[SOURCE Conference]], SOURCE is a computer security conference in Boston, Dublin and Seattle that offers education in both the business and technical aspects of the security industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sourceconference.com |title=Boston 2013 |publisher=SOURCE Conference |date=2012-04-17 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* {{Interlanguage link multi|SSTIC|fr|3=Symposium sur la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 des technologies de l'information et des communications}},<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sstic.org |title=sstic.org |publisher=sstic.org |date= |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref> Annual French Security Symposium held in [[Rennes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sstic.org |title=SSTIC2013 |publisher=Sstic.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Swiss Cyber Storm]], International IT Security Conference held in October at KKL [[Lucerne]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.swisscyberstorm.com/ |title=Swiss Cyber Storm|publisher=SCS|accessdate=2014-04-14}}</ref>\n* [[TROOPERS IT Security Conference]], Annual international IT Security event with workshops held in [[Heidelberg]], [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.troopers.de |title=The IT-Security Conference |publisher=Troopers.de |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* USENIX Security,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usenix.org/conferences/byname/108 |title=Events by Name: USENIX Security Symposium |publisher=USENIX |date=n.d.|access-date=1 November 2015}}</ref> annual security conference associated with [[USENIX]].\n* [[Virus Bulletin]] conference, annual security conference held late September or early October since 1989.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.virusbtn.com/conference |title=Virus Bulletin conference |work=Virus Bulletin|accessdate=2013-08-29}}</ref>\n* [[0SecCon]] Zero Security Conference held in [[Kerala.]]<ref name=\"0seccon.ncom\">{{cite web|url=http://0seccon.com |title=International Security Conference |publisher=E7H1C5 |date=2016-09-03 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Positive Hack Days]], Annual international IT Security event with workshops held in [[Moscow]], [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.phdays.com/en/ |title=PHDays * |publisher=PHDays.com |accessdate=2018-01-15}}</ref>\n*WIFS (Workshop on Information Forensics and Security), annual workshop hosted by [[IEEE Signal Processing Society|IEEE signal processing society]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Signal Processing Society Conferences & Workshops |url=https://signalprocessingsociety.org/events/conferences |website=IEEE Signal Processing Society |accessdate=31 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Hacker conferences==\n[[File:DEF CON 17 CTF competition.jpg|thumb|A team competing in the [[Capture the flag|CTF]] competition at [[DEF CON]] 17]]\nA '''hacker conference''', also known as a '''hacker con''', is a [[Convention (meeting)|convention]] for [[hacker (computer security)|hackers]]. These serve as meeting places for [[phreak]]ers, [[hacker (computer security)|hackers]], and [[computer security|security]] professionals.\n\nThe actual events, time-spans, and details of various themes of these conventions not only depends on the specific convention attended but also its perceived reputation. Typically the actual details of any given convention are couched in mild secrecy due to the legality of certain panels, as well as the willingness of attendees to explain themselves to law enforcement and less computer-savvy individuals (see [[hacker definition controversy]]).\n\nCommon topics include [[wardriving]], [[lockpicking]], corporate and network security, personal rights and freedoms, new technologies, as well as general 'geek' motifs. Some may also have contests and general collaborative events such as [[hackathon]]s.\n\n[[File:HackerCon Badges.jpg|thumb|right|A variety of electronic and non-electronic hacker conference badges]]\nOne facet of Hacker conferences that tends to differentiate many \"HackerCons\" from general computer security conferences, is the evolution of the conference badge. While many conferences use a fairly standard paper/plastic badge to identify attendees by name, many hacker con's have evolved to use more non-traditional badges, such as electronic PCB's with LED's, LCD screens, and can include wifi and advanced, often hidden functionality, to include games, that do not identify the individual, sometimes promoting a group identity or regional/local group affiliation. This has spurred the creation of so-called \"badgelife\" where different individuals and organizations (such as local hacker groups) may design, create, and sell or otherwise distribute a separate badge attendees wear in addition to their conference badge. These badges may be purchased, but some may have to be earned by completing a challenge at the conference. One of the rarest and most desirable badges is the [[DEF_CON#Black_Badge|DefCon Black Badge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/vbne9a/a-history-of-badgelife-def-cons-unlikely-obsession-with-artistic-circuit-boards |title=A History of Badgelife, Def Con's Unlikely Obsession with Artistic Circuit Boards |publisher=motherboard.vice.com |accessdate=2019-01-14}}</ref> While the use of the badges are traditionally associated with DefCon, their use has spread to other conferences.\n\n=== List of hacker conferences ===<!-- PLEASE RESPECT ALPHABETIAL ORDER -->\n* AthCon, the largest hacker conference in South Eastern Europe taking place annually in Athens, Greece.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athcon.org |accessdate=May 3, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100403092901/http://www.athcon.org/ |archivedate=April 3, 2010 | title=Internet Archive waybackmachine }}</ref>\n* [[Security BSides|BSides]], community conference that initially started in the US is now global.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.securitybsides.com |title=Security B-Sides |publisher=Securitybsides.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n*[https://www.blackhoodie.re/ Blackhoodie], is a series of free, women-only reverse engineering conference offering workshops and talks. They are held in different cities around the world on a regular basis to encourage women interested in the cyber security field.\n* [[CarolinaCon]], an annual [[information security]] and [[Information rights management|rights]] conference held every spring in [[North Carolina]]'s [[Research Triangle]].\n* [[Chaos Communication Congress]], the oldest and Europe's largest hacker conference, held by [[Chaos Computer Club]].\n*CircleCityCon is a security and technology conference held annually in June in [[Indianapolis]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://circlecitycon.com/|title=CircleCityCon \u2013 The Game of Pwns|website=circlecitycon.com|access-date=2016-03-24}}</ref>\n* [[Cop CON]], is a unique Cyber Policing Conference held across [[India]] every year by Indian Cyber Army.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.icalab.com/organization/about-us |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618055016/https://www.icalab.com/organization/about-us |archive-date=2016-06-18 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[CypherCon]], a [[Milwaukee]] based hacker conference held late winter each year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.CypherCon.com |title=Milwaukee's Hacking Conference |publisher=CypherCon |accessdate=2015-09-09}}</ref>\n* [[DEF CON]], in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], is the biggest hacker convention in the [[United States]] held during summer (June\u2013August).\n* [[DerbyCon]], an annual hacker conference based in Louisville, KY (2011-2019).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://infosecisland.com/blogview/17012-Wow-So-That-Was-DerbyCon.html |title=Wow! So That Was DerbyCon |publisher=Infosecisland.com |date=2011-10-03 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[The Diana Initiative|Diana Initiative]], an annual hacker conference to promote Women in cybersecurity technologies by The Diana Initiative non profit org located in Las Vegas, NV.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dianainitiative.org|title=The Diana Initiative : Hacker Family, Our diversity Unifies Us|publisher=dianainitiative.org|date=2018-02-09 |accessdate=2018-02-09}}</ref>\n* [[Ekoparty]], a hacker convention in Argentina and one of the most important in South America, held annually around September in Buenos Aires.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekoparty.com.ar |title=ekoparty Security Conference |publisher=Ekoparty.com.ar |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120325050037/http://ekoparty.com.ar/ |archive-date=2012-03-25 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[GrrCon]], an annual hacker conference hosted each September in Grand Rapids, Michigan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.infosecisland.com/blogtag/2183/GrrCON.html |title=Infosec Island |publisher=Infosec Island |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* GroundZero Summit, an annual hacker conference hosted each November in Hotel Ashoka, New Delhi.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.g0s.org|title=Ground Zero Summit|publisher=Indian InfoSec Consortium|access-date=2019-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531193815/https://g0s.org/|archive-date=2019-05-31|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Hack in the Box]], an annual hacker conference.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://packetstormsecurity.org/files/107632/HITB-2012-CFP-Europe.txt |title=Hack In The Box 2012 Europe Call For Papers |publisher=Packet Storm Security |date=2011-12-08 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Kent |first=Jonathan |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/blog/2011/may/23/hack-in-the-box-security-conference |title=Hacking conference sees 'enemies' break boundaries |publisher=Guardian |date=2011-05-23 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Hackers Day]] which was previously known as DEFCON Lucknow based in [[Lucknow]], is one of the best hacking conferences in [[India]] held frequently in January\u2013February every year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hackersday.org |title=Hackers Day International Information Security Conference|publisher=hackersday.org |accessdate=2015-04-08}}</ref>\n* [[Hackers 2 Hackers Conference (H2HC)]] is the oldest security research (hacking) conference in Latin America and one of the oldest ones still active in the world.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.800-number.info/amazon-phone-number/ |title=Amazon Phone Numbers |publisher=Malik |accessdate=2020-04-22 }}</ref>\n* [[Hackers Idol]], is a unique Hackers & Cyber Enthusiast Talent Hunt held across [[India]] every year by Indian Cyber Army.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icalab.com/hackersidol |accessdate=December 30, 2013 | title= Academy |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411173256/http://www.icalab.com/hackersidol/ |archivedate=April 11, 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[Hackers Next Door]], in [[New York City]] is held by [[Tech Learning Collective]] during the Winter (November/December).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hnd.techlearningcollective.com/|title=Hackers Next Door|publisher=[[Tech Learning Collective]]|date=|accessdate=2019-11-03}}</ref>\n* [[Hackers on Planet Earth]] (HOPE), in [[New York City]] is held by [[2600: The Hacker Quarterly]] in mid-summer (July/August) every other year.\n* [[Hackfest.ca]], in Quebec, Canada, bilingual conferences and hacking games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hackfest.ca |title=hackfest.ca |publisher=hackfest.ca |date= |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref>\n* HackMiami Conference, a hacker conference in Miami, Florida, organized by the [[HackMiami]] [[hackerspace]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hackmiami.org |title=Hackmiami |publisher=Hackmiami |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Hacktivity]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hacktivity.com |title=Hacktivity - The IT Security Festival in Central and Eastern Europe |publisher=Hacktivity |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> in [[Budapest]], Hungary, run every September, the largest hacker conference in the Central and Eastern Europe.\n*Hardwear.io - Hardware Security Conference is an annual Hardware Security event held in The Hague, Netherlands. It is being organized every year to answer the emerging threats and attacks on hardware.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hardwear.io|title=Hardware Security Conference and Training|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* [[INFILTRATE]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://infiltratecon.com |title=Infiltrate - Security Conference |publisher=Infiltratecon.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> hosted by Immunity, Inc, is a deep technical security conference that focuses on offensive technical issues. The conference has been held annually in [[Miami Beach, Florida|Miami Beach]], [[Florida]] since 2011.\n* [[Kernelcon]], is an [[Omaha]], Nebraska hacker convention held annually in April, beginning in 2019.\n* [[Kiwicon]], is a [[Wellington]], New Zealand hacker convention.\n* [[LayerOne]], held every spring in Los Angeles, California.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.layerone.org |title=LayerOne 2013 &#124; Los Angeles' premiere security conference |publisher=Layerone.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n*[[LeHack]], FRENCH HACKERS CONFERENCE hosted in Paris <ref>{{cite web|url=https://lehack.org/en |title=Call for papers |publisher=https://lehack.org/en |accessdate=2019-04-05}}</ref>\n*[[Malcon]], the world's first International Malware Conference, hosted in India.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.malcon.org |title=MalCon - Malware Conference |publisher=MalCon |date=2012-11-24 |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526164938/http://www.malcon.org/ |archive-date=2013-05-26 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*No Hat, is a computer security conference  held annually in Bergamo, Italy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nohat.it/index.html|title=No Hat 2019 {{!}} Computer Security Conference|website=No Hat 2019|access-date=2019-06-25}}</ref>\n* [[NorthSec]], in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], is an applied security event held yearly mid-May, featuring two days of conference followed by a 48h on-site [[Capture the flag#Computer security|CTF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nsec.io |title=NorthSec |publisher=NorthSec |accessdate=2014-11-21}}</ref>\n* [[Notacon]], in [[Cleveland]], [[Ohio]], is an art and technology conference held frequently in mid-April.\n* [[Nuit Du Hack]], in [[Paris]], [[France]], is the oldest and largest hacker conference held frequently in late-June.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nuitduhack.com/en |title=Call for papers |publisher=www.nuitduhack.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[PhreakNIC]], in [[Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville]], [[Tennessee]], is held by Nashville 2600.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://phreaknic.info/pn12 |title=Phreaknic 12 - October 24th - 25th, 2008 |publisher=Phreaknic.info |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130221022754/http://www.phreaknic.info/pn12/ |archive-date=2013-02-21 |url-status=dead }}</ref> around October.\n* Pumpcon, A yearly hackercon in a bar in Philadelphia, PA. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pumpcon.org/ |title=PumpCon |publisher=PumpConCon |accessdate=2019-01-14}}</ref>\n* Quahogcon, In [[Providence, Rhode Island|Providence]], [[Rhode Island]] is held at the end of April.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://quahogcon.org |title=QuahogCon |publisher=QuahogCon |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* Roadsec,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://roadsec.com.br |title=roadsec.com.br |publisher=roadsec.com.br |date= |accessdate=2017-12-14}}</ref> One of the biggest hacking conferences in Latin America, held in Brazil, with smaller city editions throughout the whole year, and a big ending edition held in S\u00e3o Paulo in November (February - November).\n* ROOTCON,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rootcon.org |title=RootCon.org |publisher=RootCon.org |date= |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref> Premier Annual Hacker Conference in the Philippines held annually during summer (September - October).\n* [[RootedCON]], in [[Madrid]], [[Spain]], is one of the biggest hacker conference in [[Europe]]. This convention started in 2010. (March)\n* [[ShellCon]], in [[Los Angeles CA]] is an information security conference that is held annually in the beautiful beach cities of Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://shellcon.io |title=ShellCon |publisher=shellcon.io |date= |accessdate=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n* [[ShmooCon]], a [[Washington DC]] convention started in 2005 by [[The Shmoo Group]], and held annually in late winter (usually February).\n* [[SkyDogCon]], A technology conference in Nashville, TN for the individual with the Renaissance Mind. SkyDogCon exists to facilitate learning, information sharing, and mingling with like-minded people in a relaxed atmosphere.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skydogcon.com/SDC2 |title=SkyDogCon |publisher=SkyDogCon |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Summercon]], one of the oldest hacker conventions, held during Summer (frequently in June). It helped set a precedent for more modern \"cons\" such as H.O.P.E. and DEF CON.\n* [[The Hackers Conference (convention)|The Hackers Conference]], is India's biggest Cyber Security Conference held in New Delhi, [[India]] every Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehackersconference.com |title=The Hackers Conference 2013 - International IT Security Conference |publisher=Thehackersconference.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[THOTCON]], a [[Chicago]] based hacker conference held in the Spring each year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thotcon.org |title=Chicago's Hacking Conference |publisher=Thotcon |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[ToorCon]], San Diego hacker convention that emerged from the 2600 user group frequently in late September.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toorcon.org |title=Information Security Conference |publisher=ToorCon |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[WildWestHackinFest]], a conference focused on training and development held in [[Deadwood, South Dakota]] in October. Explore the [[Black Hills]] and learn how to hack all the things, including the [[Internet of things|IoT]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wildwesthackinfest.com/ |title=Wild West Hackin Fest |publisher=Wild West Hackin' Fest |accessdate=2017-10-27}}</ref>\n* [[ZeroAccess]], is a unique International Cyber Security Conference held in India, [[India]] in the Month of April by Indian Cyber Army<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icalab.com/zeroaccess |accessdate=May 12, 2014 | title=Unknown}}{{dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n* Sthack is an annual security conference in [[Bordeaux]], followed by the traditional Capture The Flag.\n\n== Non-annual hacker conventions ==\n* Stichting [[HAL2001]], a not-for-profit organization, holds a quadrennial Dutch hacker convention. They have, so far, held HAL2001 (Hackers at Large) and [[What the Hack]] (2005, originally called '''HEX''' (referring to the 16th anniversary of the event, as well as an acronym for '''Hacking Extreme''')). The Dutch conferences held prior Stichting HAL2001's existence were [[Galactic Hacker Party]] (1989), [[Hacking at the End of the Universe]] (1993) and [[Hacking In Progress]] (1997), notable for being held simultaneously and in conjunction with [[Beyond HOPE]]. The not-for-profit organization 'Stichting Hxx'<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.stichtinghxx.nl/ |title=stichtinghxx.nl |publisher=stichtinghxx.nl |accessdate=2014-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100112052137/http://stichtinghxx.nl/ |archive-date=2010-01-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref>  was organizing the 2009 incarnation of this con; HAR ([[Hacking at Random]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.har2009.org |title=Hacking at Random |publisher=HAR2009 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> During the summer of 2013 the most recent installment of the series, called OHM ([[Observe. Hack. Make.|Observe Hack Make]]), was held.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ohm2013.org |title=OHM2013: Observe. Hack. Make. July 31 \u2013 August 4, 2013 |publisher=Ohm2013.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://u-sys.org/HCC Hacker Convention Comparison] based on internet connectivity and attendees\n* [https://infosectrainingevents.com/ InfoSec conferences]{{Dead link|date=November 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n* [https://wiki.zenk-security.com/doku.php?id=liste_des_evenements_cybersecurite_2019_en_france List of french non-commercial IT sycurity event in 2019.] \n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Computer Security Conference}}\n[[Category:Computer security conferences| ]]\n[[Category:Hacker conventions]]\n", "text_old": "A '''computer security conference''' is a [[Convention (meeting)|convention]] for individuals involved in [[computer security]]. They generally serve as meeting places for [[System administrator|system]] and [[network administrator]]s, [[hacker (computer security)|hacker]]s, and computer security experts.\n\n==Events==\n[[File:Michael Lynn Black Hat Briefing Las Vegas 2005.jpg|thumb|Michael Lynn, a keynote speaker at [[Black Hat Briefings]] 2005]]\nCommon activities at hacker conventions may include:\n* Presentations from keynote speakers or panels. Common topics include [[Social engineering (security)|social engineering]], [[lockpicking]], [[penetration testing]], and hacking tools.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagocon.com/content/view/33/12}}{{dead link|date=April 2013 | title=Unknown}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sxconference.com |title=SX - Security Exchange '12 |publisher=M.Tech Products |year=2012 |accessdate=2013-04-05 }}</ref>\n* Hands-on activities and competitions such as [[Capture the flag#Computer security|capture the flag]] (CTF). \n* \"Boot camps\" offering training and certification in Information Technology.<ref>[http://www.chicagocon.com/content/view/97/7] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081120004825/http://www.chicagocon.com/content/view/97/7 |date=November 20, 2008 }}</ref>\n\n===List of general computer security conferences===\nGeneral security conferences might be held by non-profit/not-for-profit/for-profit professional associations, individuals or informal group of individuals, or by security product vendor companies.\n[[File:Haroon meer keynote speaker at nullcon 2018.jpg|alt=|thumb|Haroon Meer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nullcon.net/website/goa-2018/speakers/haroon-meer.php|title=Haroon Meer|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>, a keynote speaker at nullcon 2018]]\n\n<!-- PLEASE RESPECT ALPHABETICAL ORDER -->\n* 44Con <ref>{{cite web|url=https://44con.com/ |title=44Con Website |publisher=44Con |date= |accessdate=2019-01-14}}</ref> An Infosec conference and training event that occurs annually in London, UK.\n* [[Association for Computing Machinery|ACM]]-CCS (Conferences on Computer and Communications Security),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sigsac.org/ccs.html |title=Acm Ccs |publisher=Sigsac.org |date=2012-01-23 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> security conference held since 1993.\n* [[ACSAC]], Annual Computer Security Applications Conference<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acsac.org |title=Security Conference, Security Training & Security Networking - ACSAC 2013 |publisher=ACSAC |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> - oldest information security ''conference'' held annually.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acsac.org/archive |title=Past ACSACs - Annual Computer Security Applications Conference |publisher=ACSAC |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* ASIA or the Annual Symposium on Information Assurance<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.albany.edu/iasymposium |title=Annual Symposium on Information Assurance (ASIA) |publisher=Albany.edu |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> that serves as the academic track for the [[New York (state)|New York]] State Cyber Security Conference,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cscic.state.ny.us/security/conferences |title=NYS Division of Homeland Security & Emergency Services - OCS |publisher=Cscic.state.ny.us |date=2013-02-21 |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110221112525/http://www.cscic.state.ny.us/security/conferences/ |archive-date=2011-02-21 |url-status=dead }}</ref> an annual information security conference held in [[Albany, NY]] usually for two days during June targeted at academic, government, and industry participants.\n* [[Black Hat Briefings|Black Hat]], a series of conferences held annually in different cities around the world. Black Hat USA, held in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]] immediately before [[DEF CON (convention)|DEF CON]], is one of the largest [[computer security]] events in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.blackhat.com |title=Black Hat |publisher=Black Hat |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* \n* [[BlueHat]] Conference, a twice a year, invitation-only [[Microsoft]] security conference aimed at bringing Microsoft security professionals and external security researchers together.<ref name=\"microsoft.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.microsoft.com/technet/security/bluehat/default.mspx |title=Bluehat Security Briefings |publisher=Microsoft.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref name=\"news.cnet.com\">{{cite news|url=http://news.cnet.com/Microsoft-meets-the-hackers/2009-1002_3-5747813.html |title=Microsoft meets the hackers |publisher=CNET News |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref name=\"technet.microsoft.com\">{{cite web|url=https://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/security/cc261637.aspx |title=Bluehat Security Briefings |publisher=Technet.microsoft.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Brucon]], yearly conference, previously held in [[Brussels]], since 2012 it is held in [[Ghent]]. Lasting 2 days, and preceded by a training.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brucon.org|accessdate=27 April 2015 | title=BruconTraining}}</ref>\n* [[CanSecWest]], in [[Vancouver]]  is held at the end of March and hosts the [[Pwn2Own]] hacking contest.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cansecwest.com |title=CanSecWest Applied Security Conference: Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada |publisher=Cansecwest.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Naraine |first=Ryan |url=http://www.zdnet.com/blog/security/cansecwest-pwn2own-hacker-challenge-gets-a-105000-makeover/10182 |title=CanSecWest Pwn2Own hacker challenge gets a $105,000 makeover |publisher=ZDNet |date=2012-01-23 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Mills |first=Elinor |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-27080_3-20001126-245.html |title=iPhone, Safari, IE 8, Firefox hacked in CanSecWest contest |publisher=CNET News |date=2010-03-24 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* CSS - International Conference on Cryptography and Security System<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.css.umcs.lublin.pl |title=css.umcs.lublin.pl |publisher=css.umcs.lublin.pl |date= |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref> in Poland.\n* [[DeepSec]], in [[Vienna]]  covers many security aspects of computing and electronic communications as well as security management and social aspects. DeepSec is visited by a broad international audience, academics, researchers, vendors, finance, public administration etc. (2 days trainings, 2 days conference).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ethicalhacker.net/component/option,com_smf/Itemid,54/topic,9163.0 |title=DeepSec 2012 |publisher=The Ethical Hacker Network |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121030222352/http://www.ethicalhacker.net/component/option,com_smf/Itemid,54/topic,9163.0/ |archive-date=2012-10-30 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Presentations are published on Vimeo and YouTube.\n* [[Department of Defense Cyber Crime Center#Defense Cyber Crime Conference|Department of Defense Cyber Crime Conference]], an annual conference that focuses on the computer security needs of the United States federal government, military, and defense contractors.\n* FSec - Croatian annual security conference held at the Faculty of organization and informatics in [[Vara\u017edin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fsec.foi.hr |title=FSec |publisher=FSec |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[GreHack.fr]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://grehack.fr |title=grehack.fr |publisher=grehack.fr |date=2013-11-15 |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref> an annual conference held in [[Grenoble]],. Speakers from academia, industry. Both offensive and defensive security.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grehack.fr |title=Security, Ethical Hacking conference and Capture The Flag (CTF) in Grenoble |publisher=GreHack |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Hack.lu]], an annual conference held in [[Luxembourg]]\n* [[Hacker Halted]], Presented by [[EC-Council]], the objective of the global series of Hacker Halted conferences is to raise international awareness towards increased education and ethics in IT Security.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hackerhalted.com |title=Hacker Halted 2012 |publisher=Hackerhalted.com |date=2012-09-21 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[HackinParis]], Is an annual event organized by [[SYSDREAM]]. The program includes IT security, industrial espionage, penetration testing, physical security, social engineering, forensics, malware analysis techniques and countermeasures.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hackinparis.com |title=Hack in Paris 2019 |publisher=hackinparis.com |date=2019-01-10 |accessdate=2019-01-15}}</ref>\n*[https://www.hack-it-n.com/ HACK-IT-N] is a cybersecurity conference that deals with current issues and offensive and defensive techniques of the moment: hacking, cyber-espionage, cyber-surveillance etc. It's held in Bordeaux at the end of each year and organized by [https://tehtris.com/en/home/ TEHTRIS] and the [https://enseirb-matmeca.bordeaux-inp.fr/fr ENSEIRB-MATMECA] engineering school. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hack-it-n.com/|title=HACK-IT-N|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* [[Hackito Ergo Sum]], Security conference pertaining to research topics, with attendees and speakers from both the industry, the offensive side and the academic circles, held in Paris every April.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hackitoergosum.org |title=Hackito Ergo Sum 2013 |publisher=Hackitoergosum.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[HITBSecConf / Hack In The Box]], deep-knowledge security conference held in Malaysia and the Netherlands.<ref>[http://www.conference.hitb.org conference.hitb.org] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140625153121/http://conference.hitb.org/ |date=2014-06-25 }}</ref>\n* [[ICISSP]]  International Conference on Information Systems Security and Privacy,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.icissp.org |title=ICISSP International Conference on Information Systems Security and Privacy}}</ref> \n* [[IEEE]] Symposium on Security and Privacy,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ieee-security.org/TC/SP-Index.html |title=IEEE Symposium on Security and Privacy |publisher=Ieee-security.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> top-tier privacy & security conference.\n* IIA/ISACA Chicago IT Hacking and Cybersecurity Conference, a regional, two-day event that brings together executives and professionals in audit, IT, and risk management functions to hear current trends and first-hand knowledge from subject matter experts. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://chapters.theiia.org/chicago/Events/Pages/IIA-ISACA-6th-Annual-IT-Hacking-n-Cybersecurity-Conference.aspx |title=6th Annual IIA/ISACA Chicago IT Hacking and Cybersecurity Conference |year=2019 }}</ref> \n* [[INFWARCON]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://infowarcon.com/ |title=infowarcon.com |publisher=infowarcon.com |date= |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref> Beyond Information Warfare - Offensive Cyber Weapons and Technologies Training Congress.\n* IP EXPO Europe, held annually at London's ExCeL Centre\n* IP EXPO Nordic, held annually at Stockholm's Waterfront Congress Centre\n* IWSECC International Workshop on Security Engineering for Cloud Computing in conjunction with the 14th International Conference on Availability, Reliability and Security (ARES \u2013 http://www.ares-conference.eu)\n* LeetCon, IT-Security-Convention in Hannover (Germany), frequently October or November every Year. Talks about IT-Security, IoT, Industry 4.0 and more.\n* NDSS (Network & Distributed System Security Symposium),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.internetsociety.org/events/ndss-symposium |title=NDSS Network & Distributed System Security Symposium |publisher=Internet Society |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> annual security conference from Internet Society.\n* NSPW (New Security Paradigms Workshop),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nspw.org |title=Introduction &#124; New Security Paradigms Workshop |publisher=Nspw.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> a workshop with new ideas in security.\n* nullcon Security Conference is an annual security event held in Goa, India.<ref name=\"nulcon.net\">{{cite web|url=http://nullcon.net |title=International Security Conference |publisher=nullcon |date=2013-03-02 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref name=\"zeenews.india.com\">{{cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/net-news/cyber-experts-show-vulnerability-of-gsm-networks_759318.html |title=Cyber experts show vulnerability of GSM networks |publisher=Zeenews.india.com |date=2012-02-19 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[OWASP|Open Web Application Security Project (OWASP)]], Focuses on web application security.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appsecusa.org |title=Appsec USA 2013 |publisher=OWASP |year=2013 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[REcon]] REcon is a computer security conference with a focus on reverse engineering and advanced exploitation techniques.\n* [[RSA Conference|RSA Security Conference]], Cryptography and information security-related conference held annually in the San Francisco Bay Area.\n* [[RuhrSec]], annual non-profit security conference at the Ruhr University Bochum.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ruhrsec.de/ |title=RuhrSec Conference |publisher=Hackmanit |year=2017 |accessdate=2017-01-05}}</ref>\n* [[S4:SCADA Security Scientific Symposium]], Security conference pertaining to SCADA held annually by Digital Bond, usually in [[Miami]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalbond.com/index.php/events |title=ICS Security Event Calendar |publisher=Digitalbond.com |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101228203154/http://www.digitalbond.com/index.php/events/ |archive-date=2010-12-28 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* SecurIT 2012, International Conference on Security of [[Internet of Things]] held in mid of August at [[Amrita Vishwa Vidyapeetham]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.securit.ws |title=SecurIT 2012 - Cyber Security conference on IoT |publisher=Securit.ws |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* SecureWorld Expo, a series of IT Security conferences offering education, CPE training opportunities, and networking of security leaders, experts, senior executives, and policy makers who shape the face of security.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.secureworldexpo.com |title=SecureWorld Conferences |publisher=Seguro Group |work=SecureWorld Post |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[SIN ACM]], or the International Conference on Security of Information and Networks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sinconf.org |title= the International Conference on Security of Information and Networks (SINCONF)}}</ref>\n* [[SOURCE Conference]], SOURCE is a computer security conference in Boston, Dublin and Seattle that offers education in both the business and technical aspects of the security industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sourceconference.com |title=Boston 2013 |publisher=SOURCE Conference |date=2012-04-17 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* {{Interlanguage link multi|SSTIC|fr|3=Symposium sur la s\u00e9curit\u00e9 des technologies de l'information et des communications}},<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sstic.org |title=sstic.org |publisher=sstic.org |date= |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref> Annual French Security Symposium held in [[Rennes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sstic.org |title=SSTIC2013 |publisher=Sstic.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Swiss Cyber Storm]], International IT Security Conference held in October at KKL [[Lucerne]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.swisscyberstorm.com/ |title=Swiss Cyber Storm|publisher=SCS|accessdate=2014-04-14}}</ref>\n* [[TROOPERS IT Security Conference]], Annual international IT Security event with workshops held in [[Heidelberg]], [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.troopers.de |title=The IT-Security Conference |publisher=Troopers.de |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* USENIX Security,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usenix.org/conferences/byname/108 |title=Events by Name: USENIX Security Symposium |publisher=USENIX |date=n.d.|access-date=1 November 2015}}</ref> annual security conference associated with [[USENIX]].\n* [[Virus Bulletin]] conference, annual security conference held late September or early October since 1989.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.virusbtn.com/conference |title=Virus Bulletin conference |work=Virus Bulletin|accessdate=2013-08-29}}</ref>\n* [[0SecCon]] Zero Security Conference held in [[Kerala.]]<ref name=\"0seccon.ncom\">{{cite web|url=http://0seccon.com |title=International Security Conference |publisher=E7H1C5 |date=2016-09-03 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Positive Hack Days]], Annual international IT Security event with workshops held in [[Moscow]], [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.phdays.com/en/ |title=PHDays * |publisher=PHDays.com |accessdate=2018-01-15}}</ref>\n*WIFS (Workshop on Information Forensics and Security), annual workshop hosted by [[IEEE Signal Processing Society|IEEE signal processing society]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Signal Processing Society Conferences & Workshops |url=https://signalprocessingsociety.org/events/conferences |website=IEEE Signal Processing Society |accessdate=31 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Hacker conferences==\n[[File:DEF CON 17 CTF competition.jpg|thumb|A team competing in the [[Capture the flag|CTF]] competition at [[DEF CON]] 17]]\nA '''hacker conference''', also known as a '''hacker con''', is a [[Convention (meeting)|convention]] for [[hacker (computer security)|hackers]]. These serve as meeting places for [[phreak]]ers, [[hacker (computer security)|hackers]], and [[computer security|security]] professionals.\n\nThe actual events, time-spans, and details of various themes of these conventions not only depends on the specific convention attended but also its perceived reputation. Typically the actual details of any given convention are couched in mild secrecy due to the legality of certain panels, as well as the willingness of attendees to explain themselves to law enforcement and less computer-savvy individuals (see [[hacker definition controversy]]).\n\nCommon topics include [[wardriving]], [[lockpicking]], corporate and network security, personal rights and freedoms, new technologies, as well as general 'geek' motifs. Some may also have contests and general collaborative events such as [[hackathon]]s.\n\n[[File:HackerCon Badges.jpg|thumb|right|A variety of electronic and non-electronic hacker conference badges]]\nOne facet of Hacker conferences that tends to differentiate many \"HackerCons\" from general computer security conferences, is the evolution of the conference badge. While many conferences use a fairly standard paper/plastic badge to identify attendees by name, many hacker con's have evolved to use more non-traditional badges, such as electronic PCB's with LED's, LCD screens, and can include wifi and advanced, often hidden functionality, to include games, that do not identify the individual, sometimes promoting a group identity or regional/local group affiliation. This has spurred the creation of so-called \"badgelife\" where different individuals and organizations (such as local hacker groups) may design, create, and sell or otherwise distribute a separate badge attendees wear in addition to their conference badge. These badges may be purchased, but some may have to be earned by completing a challenge at the conference. One of the rarest and most desirable badges is the [[DEF_CON#Black_Badge|DefCon Black Badge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/vbne9a/a-history-of-badgelife-def-cons-unlikely-obsession-with-artistic-circuit-boards |title=A History of Badgelife, Def Con's Unlikely Obsession with Artistic Circuit Boards |publisher=motherboard.vice.com |accessdate=2019-01-14}}</ref> While the use of the badges are traditionally associated with DefCon, their use has spread to other conferences.\n\n=== List of hacker conferences ===<!-- PLEASE RESPECT ALPHABETIAL ORDER -->\n* AthCon, the largest hacker conference in South Eastern Europe taking place annually in Athens, Greece.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athcon.org |accessdate=May 3, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100403092901/http://www.athcon.org/ |archivedate=April 3, 2010 | title=Internet Archive waybackmachine }}</ref>\n* [[Security BSides|BSides]], community conference that initially started in the US is now global.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.securitybsides.com |title=Security B-Sides |publisher=Securitybsides.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n*[https://www.blackhoodie.re/ Blackhoodie], is a series of free, women-only reverse engineering conference offering workshops and talks. They are held in different cities around the world on a regular basis to encourage women interested in the cyber security field.\n* [[CarolinaCon]], an annual [[information security]] and [[Information rights management|rights]] conference held every spring in [[North Carolina]]'s [[Research Triangle]].\n* [[Chaos Communication Congress]], the oldest and Europe's largest hacker conference, held by [[Chaos Computer Club]].\n*CircleCityCon is a security and technology conference held annually in June in [[Indianapolis]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://circlecitycon.com/|title=CircleCityCon \u2013 The Game of Pwns|website=circlecitycon.com|access-date=2016-03-24}}</ref>\n* [[Cop CON]], is a unique Cyber Policing Conference held across [[India]] every year by Indian Cyber Army.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.icalab.com/organization/about-us |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-04-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160618055016/https://www.icalab.com/organization/about-us |archive-date=2016-06-18 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[CypherCon]], a [[Milwaukee]] based hacker conference held late winter each year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.CypherCon.com |title=Milwaukee's Hacking Conference |publisher=CypherCon |accessdate=2015-09-09}}</ref>\n* [[DEF CON]], in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], is the biggest hacker convention in the [[United States]] held during summer (June\u2013August).\n* [[DerbyCon]], an annual hacker conference based in Louisville, KY (2011-2019).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://infosecisland.com/blogview/17012-Wow-So-That-Was-DerbyCon.html |title=Wow! So That Was DerbyCon |publisher=Infosecisland.com |date=2011-10-03 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[The Diana Initiative|Diana Initiative]], an annual hacker conference to promote Women in cybersecurity technologies by The Diana Initiative non profit org located in Las Vegas, NV.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dianainitiative.org|title=The Diana Initiative : Hacker Family, Our diversity Unifies Us|publisher=dianainitiative.org|date=2018-02-09 |accessdate=2018-02-09}}</ref>\n* [[Ekoparty]], a hacker convention in Argentina and one of the most important in South America, held annually around September in Buenos Aires.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ekoparty.com.ar |title=ekoparty Security Conference |publisher=Ekoparty.com.ar |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120325050037/http://ekoparty.com.ar/ |archive-date=2012-03-25 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[GrrCon]], an annual hacker conference hosted each September in Grand Rapids, Michigan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.infosecisland.com/blogtag/2183/GrrCON.html |title=Infosec Island |publisher=Infosec Island |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* GroundZero Summit, an annual hacker conference hosted each November in Hotel Ashoka, New Delhi.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.g0s.org|title=Ground Zero Summit|publisher=Indian InfoSec Consortium|access-date=2019-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531193815/https://g0s.org/|archive-date=2019-05-31|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Hack in the Box]], an annual hacker conference.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://packetstormsecurity.org/files/107632/HITB-2012-CFP-Europe.txt |title=Hack In The Box 2012 Europe Call For Papers |publisher=Packet Storm Security |date=2011-12-08 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Kent |first=Jonathan |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/blog/2011/may/23/hack-in-the-box-security-conference |title=Hacking conference sees 'enemies' break boundaries |publisher=Guardian |date=2011-05-23 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Hackers Day]] which was previously known as DEFCON Lucknow based in [[Lucknow]], is one of the best hacking conferences in [[India]] held frequently in January\u2013February every year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hackersday.org |title=Hackers Day International Information Security Conference|publisher=hackersday.org |accessdate=2015-04-08}}</ref>\n* [[Hackers 2 Hackers Conference (H2HC)]] is the oldest security research (hacking) conference in Latin America and one of the oldest ones still active in the world.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.h2hc.org.br/h2hc/e/ |title=H2HC 10th Edition |publisher=H2hc.org.br |accessdate=2013-04-05 }}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n* [[Hackers Idol]], is a unique Hackers & Cyber Enthusiast Talent Hunt held across [[India]] every year by Indian Cyber Army.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icalab.com/hackersidol |accessdate=December 30, 2013 | title= Academy |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411173256/http://www.icalab.com/hackersidol/ |archivedate=April 11, 2014 }}</ref>\n* [[Hackers Next Door]], in [[New York City]] is held by [[Tech Learning Collective]] during the Winter (November/December).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hnd.techlearningcollective.com/|title=Hackers Next Door|publisher=[[Tech Learning Collective]]|date=|accessdate=2019-11-03}}</ref>\n* [[Hackers on Planet Earth]] (HOPE), in [[New York City]] is held by [[2600: The Hacker Quarterly]] in mid-summer (July/August) every other year.\n* [[Hackfest.ca]], in Quebec, Canada, bilingual conferences and hacking games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hackfest.ca |title=hackfest.ca |publisher=hackfest.ca |date= |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref>\n* HackMiami Conference, a hacker conference in Miami, Florida, organized by the [[HackMiami]] [[hackerspace]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hackmiami.org |title=Hackmiami |publisher=Hackmiami |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Hacktivity]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hacktivity.com |title=Hacktivity - The IT Security Festival in Central and Eastern Europe |publisher=Hacktivity |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> in [[Budapest]], Hungary, run every September, the largest hacker conference in the Central and Eastern Europe.\n*Hardwear.io - Hardware Security Conference is an annual Hardware Security event held in The Hague, Netherlands. It is being organized every year to answer the emerging threats and attacks on hardware.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hardwear.io|title=Hardware Security Conference and Training|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n* [[INFILTRATE]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://infiltratecon.com |title=Infiltrate - Security Conference |publisher=Infiltratecon.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> hosted by Immunity, Inc, is a deep technical security conference that focuses on offensive technical issues. The conference has been held annually in [[Miami Beach, Florida|Miami Beach]], [[Florida]] since 2011.\n* [[Kernelcon]], is an [[Omaha]], Nebraska hacker convention held annually in April, beginning in 2019.\n* [[Kiwicon]], is a [[Wellington]], New Zealand hacker convention.\n* [[LayerOne]], held every spring in Los Angeles, California.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.layerone.org |title=LayerOne 2013 &#124; Los Angeles' premiere security conference |publisher=Layerone.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n*[[LeHack]], FRENCH HACKERS CONFERENCE hosted in Paris <ref>{{cite web|url=https://lehack.org/en |title=Call for papers |publisher=https://lehack.org/en |accessdate=2019-04-05}}</ref>\n*[[Malcon]], the world's first International Malware Conference, hosted in India.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.malcon.org |title=MalCon - Malware Conference |publisher=MalCon |date=2012-11-24 |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526164938/http://www.malcon.org/ |archive-date=2013-05-26 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*No Hat, is a computer security conference  held annually in Bergamo, Italy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nohat.it/index.html|title=No Hat 2019 {{!}} Computer Security Conference|website=No Hat 2019|access-date=2019-06-25}}</ref>\n* [[NorthSec]], in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], is an applied security event held yearly mid-May, featuring two days of conference followed by a 48h on-site [[Capture the flag#Computer security|CTF]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nsec.io |title=NorthSec |publisher=NorthSec |accessdate=2014-11-21}}</ref>\n* [[Notacon]], in [[Cleveland]], [[Ohio]], is an art and technology conference held frequently in mid-April.\n* [[Nuit Du Hack]], in [[Paris]], [[France]], is the oldest and largest hacker conference held frequently in late-June.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nuitduhack.com/en |title=Call for papers |publisher=www.nuitduhack.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[PhreakNIC]], in [[Nashville, Tennessee|Nashville]], [[Tennessee]], is held by Nashville 2600.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://phreaknic.info/pn12 |title=Phreaknic 12 - October 24th - 25th, 2008 |publisher=Phreaknic.info |accessdate=2013-04-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130221022754/http://www.phreaknic.info/pn12/ |archive-date=2013-02-21 |url-status=dead }}</ref> around October.\n* Pumpcon, A yearly hackercon in a bar in Philadelphia, PA. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pumpcon.org/ |title=PumpCon |publisher=PumpConCon |accessdate=2019-01-14}}</ref>\n* Quahogcon, In [[Providence, Rhode Island|Providence]], [[Rhode Island]] is held at the end of April.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://quahogcon.org |title=QuahogCon |publisher=QuahogCon |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* Roadsec,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://roadsec.com.br |title=roadsec.com.br |publisher=roadsec.com.br |date= |accessdate=2017-12-14}}</ref> One of the biggest hacking conferences in Latin America, held in Brazil, with smaller city editions throughout the whole year, and a big ending edition held in S\u00e3o Paulo in November (February - November).\n* ROOTCON,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rootcon.org |title=RootCon.org |publisher=RootCon.org |date= |accessdate=2014-07-17}}</ref> Premier Annual Hacker Conference in the Philippines held annually during summer (September - October).\n* [[RootedCON]], in [[Madrid]], [[Spain]], is one of the biggest hacker conference in [[Europe]]. This convention started in 2010. (March)\n* [[ShellCon]], in [[Los Angeles CA]] is an information security conference that is held annually in the beautiful beach cities of Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://shellcon.io |title=ShellCon |publisher=shellcon.io |date= |accessdate=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n* [[ShmooCon]], a [[Washington DC]] convention started in 2005 by [[The Shmoo Group]], and held annually in late winter (usually February).\n* [[SkyDogCon]], A technology conference in Nashville, TN for the individual with the Renaissance Mind. SkyDogCon exists to facilitate learning, information sharing, and mingling with like-minded people in a relaxed atmosphere.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skydogcon.com/SDC2 |title=SkyDogCon |publisher=SkyDogCon |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[Summercon]], one of the oldest hacker conventions, held during Summer (frequently in June). It helped set a precedent for more modern \"cons\" such as H.O.P.E. and DEF CON.\n* [[The Hackers Conference (convention)|The Hackers Conference]], is India's biggest Cyber Security Conference held in New Delhi, [[India]] every Year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehackersconference.com |title=The Hackers Conference 2013 - International IT Security Conference |publisher=Thehackersconference.com |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[THOTCON]], a [[Chicago]] based hacker conference held in the Spring each year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thotcon.org |title=Chicago's Hacking Conference |publisher=Thotcon |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[ToorCon]], San Diego hacker convention that emerged from the 2600 user group frequently in late September.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toorcon.org |title=Information Security Conference |publisher=ToorCon |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n* [[WildWestHackinFest]], a conference focused on training and development held in [[Deadwood, South Dakota]] in October. Explore the [[Black Hills]] and learn how to hack all the things, including the [[Internet of things|IoT]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wildwesthackinfest.com/ |title=Wild West Hackin Fest |publisher=Wild West Hackin' Fest |accessdate=2017-10-27}}</ref>\n* [[ZeroAccess]], is a unique International Cyber Security Conference held in India, [[India]] in the Month of April by Indian Cyber Army<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.icalab.com/zeroaccess |accessdate=May 12, 2014 | title=Unknown}}{{dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n* Sthack is an annual security conference in [[Bordeaux]], followed by the traditional Capture The Flag.\n\n== Non-annual hacker conventions ==\n* Stichting [[HAL2001]], a not-for-profit organization, holds a quadrennial Dutch hacker convention. They have, so far, held HAL2001 (Hackers at Large) and [[What the Hack]] (2005, originally called '''HEX''' (referring to the 16th anniversary of the event, as well as an acronym for '''Hacking Extreme''')). The Dutch conferences held prior Stichting HAL2001's existence were [[Galactic Hacker Party]] (1989), [[Hacking at the End of the Universe]] (1993) and [[Hacking In Progress]] (1997), notable for being held simultaneously and in conjunction with [[Beyond HOPE]]. The not-for-profit organization 'Stichting Hxx'<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.stichtinghxx.nl/ |title=stichtinghxx.nl |publisher=stichtinghxx.nl |accessdate=2014-07-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100112052137/http://stichtinghxx.nl/ |archive-date=2010-01-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref>  was organizing the 2009 incarnation of this con; HAR ([[Hacking at Random]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.har2009.org |title=Hacking at Random |publisher=HAR2009 |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref> During the summer of 2013 the most recent installment of the series, called OHM ([[Observe. Hack. Make.|Observe Hack Make]]), was held.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ohm2013.org |title=OHM2013: Observe. Hack. Make. July 31 \u2013 August 4, 2013 |publisher=Ohm2013.org |accessdate=2013-04-05}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://u-sys.org/HCC Hacker Convention Comparison] based on internet connectivity and attendees\n* [https://infosectrainingevents.com/ InfoSec conferences]{{Dead link|date=November 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n* [https://wiki.zenk-security.com/doku.php?id=liste_des_evenements_cybersecurite_2019_en_france List of french non-commercial IT sycurity event in 2019.] \n\n{{