{"title_page": "Bank Employees Federation of India", "text_new": "{{short description|Bank trade union}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{unreferenced|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox Union\n|image= Befi logo.jpg\n|name= BEFI\n|country= [[India]]\n|affiliation=BANK EMPLOYEES FEDERATION OF INDIA \n|members= 125000\n|full_name= Bank Employees Federation of India\n|native_name= BEFI\n|founded= 1982\n|current= \n|head= \n|dissolved_date= \n|dissolved_state= \n|merged_into= \n|office= Naresh Paul Centre, 53 Radha Bazar Lane, Kolkata 700001, India\n|people= [[C.J.Nandakumar]], President <br> [[Debasish Basu Chowdhury]], General Secretary\n|website= {{URL|befi.in}}\n|footnotes= \n}}\n'''Bank Employees Federation of India (BEFI)''' is a bank trade union consisting of employees of commercial banks, [[Reserve Bank of India]], [[NABARD]], regional rural banks and co-operative banks. The federation espouses the causes concerning service conditions of bank employees, development of the banking industry, defense of public sector banking in [[India]] and exemplary service to customers, including the marginal and neglected. It is focused for the betterment of the working class and for India's economic and political independence.{{Citation needed|reason=No source|date=September 2019}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.befi.in/|title=BEFI|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Affiliations and groups==\nBEFI is not affiliated with any Central Trade Union of the country, but it has fraternal relations with Centre of India Trade Unions (CITU). CITU is the Trade Union front of [[Communist Party of India]] (Marxist). BEFI has strong presence in India in the States of [[Assam]], [[Bihar]], [[Himachal Pradesh]], [[Jharkhand]], [[Kerala]], [[Orissa]], [[Tripura]], [[West Bengal]], Punjab, Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh, Telangana, Karnataka etc. Among the Nationalised Bank employees, BEFI is the third largest organisation. AIBEA(All India Bank Employees Association) and NCBE(National Confederation of Bank Employees) occupy first two positions. But in Regional Rural Banks BEFI affiliates represent the majority workforce.{{Citation needed|reason=No source|date=September 2019}}\n\nIndian Bank Employees Association, an affiliate of Bank Employees Federation of India is running a school (INDIAN BANK EMPLOYEES ASSOCIATION(TAMILNADU) HIGH SCHOOL) at Kurichi village near Pattukottai in Thanjavur District, Tamil Nadu.  This school was established in the year 2002 and in just 8 years of its existence, the school has won many accolades including the honour of a science project done by the students being selected for the prestigious National Children's Science Congress.\n\n== Foundation of BEFI ==\nThe Foundation Conference of Bank Employees Federation of India was held in Calcutta on 13 to 16 October 1982. It was attended by delegates and observers from 9 State-level organizations and 4 All India Bankwise Unions. The inaugural session was held on 13 October at Subodh Mallick Square preceded by processions from BBD Bagh and various other zones. Inauguration of the Conference was done by veteran Trade Union leader B.T. Ranadive, President of\nCITU. Delegates session was inaugurated on 14 October 1982 by Jyoti Basu, Vice-President, CITU, and Chief Minister of West Bengal.{{Citation needed|reason=No source|date=September 2019}}\n\n= Central Committee Members =\n'''PRESIDENT'''\n\nC. J. Nandakumar, 36/972\u00a0 Naresh Paul Centre, Near Lissie Hospital, Ernakulam, Kerala - 682018.  \n\n\n'''VICE-PRESIDENTS'''\n\n1. Pradip Biswas, 230/2, Raipur Road, Kolkata - 700047. \n\n2. Joydeb Dasgupta, C/o. UCO Bank Emp. Association, UCO Bank, 10 Brabourne Road, Kolkata - 700001. \n\n3. Dinesh Ch. Kakati, Uco Bank, Fancy Bazar, Guwahati - 781001.\n\n4. J. P. Dixit, C/o. BEF-Bihar, Saboo Complex, 2nd Floor, Exhibition Road, Patna - 800001.\n\n5. K. Srinivasa Babu, Flat no 405, Sowmya Spring